Happy birthday.
- Don't remind me.

48
00:05:15.386 --> 00:05:17.612
Bella. your birth is definitely
something to celebrate.

49
00:05:17.996 --> 00:05:20.878
But my aging is not.
- Your aging?

50
00:05:22.914 --> 00:05:25.408
I think 18 is all youngster.
don't worry about that.

51
00:05:25.562 --> 00:05:27.136
It's one year older than you.

52
00:05:27.252 --> 00:05:28.173
No. it isn't.

53
00:05:28.327 --> 00:05:30.555
I'm a hundred and nine.
- Wow!

54
00:05:31.013 --> 00:05:33.126
Maybe I should not be dating
such an old man.

55
00:05:33.433 --> 00:05:34.125
It's gross!

56
00:05:34.202 --> 00:05:36.812
I should feel certainly repulse.

57
00:05:47.834 --> 00:05:50.444
We have to go to class.
- Yeah.

58
00:05:54.668 --> 00:05:56.128
Wait a second.

59
00:05:57.049 --> 00:05:58.623
Someone wants you.

60
00:05:59.353 --> 00:06:01.579
Bella.
- Jacob!

61
00:06:04.614 --> 00:06:06.072
I'll leave you to talk.

62
00:06:10.527 --> 00:06:12.101
Hello. biceps!

63
00:06:12.218 --> 00:06:14.943
You know. anabolic steroids are
really bad for you.

64
00:06:15.325 --> 00:06:17.170
Well. I'm just filling out. Bella.

65
00:06:17.706 --> 00:06:20.703
You know. wouldn't seem so drastic
if we hung out more.

66
00:06:21.316 --> 00:06:22.507
We should switch schools.

67
00:06:22.659 --> 00:06:24.120
Then you can come hang out
with the pale faces.

68
00:06:24.158 --> 00:06:25.080
I'm alright.

69
00:06:25.233 --> 00:06:27.576
I prefer the Res school's exclusivity.

70
00:06:28.420 --> 00:06:30.340
They let any old rift raft into this place.

71
00:06:30.570 --> 00:06:32.529
I see.
Why are you summing it?

72
00:06:32.644 --> 00:06:34.986
I was just buying a part for the Rabbit.

73
00:06:35.102 --> 00:06:37.520
You should really come. take a ride.
when it's done.

74
00:06:37.635 --> 00:06:41.784
Is it fast?
- Huh. it's decent.

75
00:06:42.973 --> 00:06:45.278
Okay.
- Okay. good.

76
00:06:45.815 --> 00:06:48.042
Hey. happy birthday.

77
00:06:49.347 --> 00:06:51.191
Your Dad told my Dad.
So...

78
00:06:52.035 --> 00:06:53.878
Yeah. of course. he did.

79
00:06:54.454 --> 00:06:57.450
I saw this the other day and
thought of you.

80
00:06:58.448 --> 00:07:00.291
It catches bad dreams.

81
00:07:02.020 --> 00:07:03.861
It's perfect.

82
00:07:05.935 --> 00:07:09.084
Thank you.
- No problem.

83
00:07:11.427 --> 00:07:13.846
See you soon. Bye.
- Yeah. see you later.

84
00:07:15.073 --> 00:07:18.070
So. how come Jacob Black gets to
give you a gift and I don't?

85
00:07:19.683 --> 00:07:21.526
Because I have nothing
to give back to you.

86
00:07:23.177 --> 00:07:25.788
Bella. you give me everything
just by breathing.

87
00:07:27.822 --> 00:07:30.626
See? Thank you.
That's all I want.

88
00:07:30.664 --> 00:07:31.816
Bella!

89
00:07:33.352 --> 00:07:35.195
Happy Birthday!
- Shhh!

90
00:07:38.190 --> 00:07:39.342
I thought. I said you.
no presents.

91
00:07:39.381 --> 00:07:41.339
I've already seen you open it
and guess what?

92
00:07:41.570 --> 00:07:42.759
You love it!

93
00:07:42.991 --> 00:07:45.218
You're gonna wear it tonight.
our house.

94
00:07:47.290 --> 00:07:50.363
Come on. please?
It will be fun.

95
00:07:53.742 --> 00:07:57.773
Okay. alright.
- Great! Okay. I'll see you at 7:00.

96
00:08:00.193 --> 00:08:03.494
Jasper. no fair
with the mood control thing.

97
00:08:04.416 --> 00:08:05.606
Sorry. Bella.

98
00:08:06.029 --> 00:08:07.220
Happy...

99
00:08:08.256 --> 00:08:09.446
Never mind.

100
00:08:11.749 --> 00:08:13.595
You can't trust vampires.

101
00:08:14.131 --> 00:08:15.206
Trust me!

102
00:08:15.552 --> 00:08:18.163
<i>O. my love!
My wife!</i>

103
00:08:18.586 --> 00:08:20.813
<i>Death that hath sucked
the honey of thy breath.</i>

104
00:08:20.890 --> 00:08:23.309
<i>Hath had no power yet
upon thy beauty.</i>

105
00:08:24.037 --> 00:08:25.920
<i>Thou art not conquered.</i>

106
00:08:27.224 --> 00:08:31.563
<i>Beauty's ensign yet is crimson in thy lips
and in thy cheeks.</i>

107
00:08:31.833 --> 00:08:34.444
<i>And death's pale flag
is not advanced there.</i>

108
00:08:34.675 --> 00:08:36.787
<i>I hate being celebrated.</i>

109
00:08:37.248 --> 00:08:38.437
<i>There are worse tragedies.</i>

110
00:08:38.514 --> 00:08:39.706
<i>Hm. look at Romeo.</i>

111
00:08:40.204 --> 00:08:43.199
<i>He kills his true love
out of sheer stupidity.</i>

112
00:08:44.811 --> 00:08:45.618
Yeah.

113
00:08:46.118 --> 00:08:47.959
Though I do envy him.
one thing.

114
00:08:50.341 --> 00:08:51.994
Juliet. She's like perfect.

115
00:08:52.222 --> 00:08:54.911
If you like that obviously
beautiful sort of thing.

116
00:08:58.558 --> 00:09:00.017
No. not the girl. dear.

117
00:09:00.939 --> 00:09:02.359
The suicide.

118
00:09:05.163 --> 00:09:07.390
It's nearly impossible for...

119
00:09:08.696 --> 00:09:11.960
...some people.

120
00:09:13.917 --> 00:09:17.297
For humans.
a little poison...

121
00:09:18.948 --> 00:09:20.790
...a dagger to the heart...

122
00:09:22.096 --> 00:09:23.940
So many different options.

123
00:09:27.703 --> 00:09:29.547
Why would you say that?

124
00:09:30.813 --> 00:09:32.655
Because I considered it once.

125
00:09:34.999 --> 00:09:37.110
I didn't know.
if I'd get to you in time.

126
00:09:37.687 --> 00:09:40.067
I had to come up with
some kind of...

127
00:09:40.259 --> 00:09:41.451
...plan.

128
00:09:42.141 --> 00:09:43.599
And what was the plan?

129
00:09:43.793 --> 00:09:45.481
I would go to Italy.

130
00:09:45.943 --> 00:09:47.785
...and provoke the Volturi.

131
00:09:47.862 --> 00:09:50.165
The what?
- The Volturi...

132
00:09:50.204 --> 00:09:53.315
Now. who would like to repeat
the last few lines...

133
00:09:53.391 --> 00:09:55.504
just to show.
they were paying attention?

134
00:09:56.385 --> 00:09:57.576
Mr. Cullen.

135
00:10:00.303 --> 00:10:02.146
Oh. yes. Mr. Birdy.

136
00:10:04.834 --> 00:10:06.064
O. here.

137
00:10:06.907 --> 00:10:09.134
Will I set up my everlasting rest.

138
00:10:10.632 --> 00:10:14.511
And shake the yoke of inauspicious stars
from this world-wearied flesh.

139
00:10:15.048 --> 00:10:16.891
Eyes. look your last!

140
00:10:17.622 --> 00:10:20.040
Arms. take your last embrace!

141
00:10:20.846 --> 00:10:23.956
And lips. O you.
the doors of breath.

142
00:10:24.148 --> 00:10:25.722
...seal with a righteous kiss.

143
00:10:25.799 --> 00:10:28.411
A dateless bargain to engrossing death!

144
00:10:30.367 --> 00:10:32.327
Eyes on the screen. people.

145
00:10:33.978 --> 00:10:36.973
<i>Thus with a kiss I die.</i>

146
00:10:39.393 --> 00:10:42.964
The Volturi are a very old.
very powerful family.

147
00:10:43.117 --> 00:10:45.921
I guess. the closest thing to royalty
my world has.

148
00:10:47.112 --> 00:10:49.722
Is that Carlisle?
- Yeah.

149
00:10:50.492 --> 00:10:52.333
He lived with them
for a few decades.

150
00:10:52.525 --> 00:10:54.752
Described them as
very refined.

151
00:10:55.252 --> 00:10:58.015
No respect for human life.
of course. but...

152
00:10:58.092 --> 00:11:01.051
...respect for the arts
and science as at least.

153
00:11:02.778 --> 00:11:04.352
<i>And the law...</i>

154
00:11:05.273 --> 00:11:07.116
<i>...above all of law.</i>

155
00:11:09.842 --> 00:11:11.686
<i>And vampires have laws?</i>

156
00:11:13.145 --> 00:11:14.988
<i>Not very many.</i>

157
00:11:15.719 --> 00:11:18.982
<i>There's only one and
it's regularly enforced.</i>

158
00:11:20.900 --> 00:11:22.361
<i>What is it?</i>

159
00:11:23.359 --> 00:11:26.353
<i>To keep the existence
of our kind a secret.</i>

160
00:11:26.776 --> 00:11:30.270
<i>We don't make spectacles
of ourselves.</i>

161
00:11:31.461 --> 00:11:34.457
<i>And we don't kill conspicuously.</i>

162
00:11:37.720 --> 00:11:39.677
<i>Unless. of course.
you want to die.</i>

163
00:11:53.887 --> 00:11:55.728
We have to talking about that.

164
00:11:55.844 --> 00:11:57.688
I can't even think...

165
00:11:58.493 --> 00:12:00.298
...about someone hurting you.

166
00:12:01.949 --> 00:12:06.480
Bella. the only thing that
can hurt me is you.

167
00:12:08.131 --> 00:12:10.243
And I don't have anything else
to be afraid of.

168
00:12:10.628 --> 00:12:11.818
That's not true.

169
00:12:14.045 --> 00:12:16.656
Victoria?
She will come for me one day.

170
00:12:17.770 --> 00:12:19.882
Alice will see
what she decides and...

171
00:12:21.110 --> 00:12:23.530
...we will be ready.
- I can protect you.

172
00:12:24.873 --> 00:12:26.447
If you change me.

173
00:12:27.215 --> 00:12:29.827
Bella. you already do protect me.

174
00:12:31.478 --> 00:12:33.320
You're my only reason...

175
00:12:34.933 --> 00:12:38.966
...to stay alive.
if that's what I am.

176
00:12:41.270 --> 00:12:43.381
But it's my job to protect you.

177
00:12:46.991 --> 00:12:50.256
From everyone except my sister.

178
00:12:50.333 --> 00:12:51.407
It's time!

179
00:12:51.483 --> 00:12:53.327
It's time! It's time!
It's time!

180
00:13:03.426 --> 00:13:06.420
Sorry about all this.
We tried to rein Alice in.

181
00:13:06.535 --> 00:13:07.801
Like it's even possible.

182
00:13:07.880 --> 00:13:10.644
Happy big Birthday. Bella!
- Thanks.

183
00:13:13.102 --> 00:13:16.173
I found it in your bag. mind?

184
00:13:16.558 --> 00:13:18.938
Dating an older woman?
Hot!

185
00:13:20.859 --> 00:13:21.779
What?

186
00:13:21.895 --> 00:13:23.354
You first. Rosalie.

187
00:13:25.850 --> 00:13:27.309
It's a necklace.

188
00:13:27.693 --> 00:13:30.073
Alice picked it up.
- Thanks.

189
00:13:32.993 --> 00:13:34.682
Show me the love!

190
00:13:38.368 --> 00:13:39.903
This is from Emmett.

191
00:13:42.592 --> 00:13:44.435
Already installed it in your truck.

192
00:13:44.972 --> 00:13:46.932
Finally. a decent sound system
for that piece of...

193
00:13:46.970 --> 00:13:49.120
Hey. don't... don't hate the truck.

194
00:13:49.810 --> 00:13:51.270
Open Esme and Carlisle's.

195
00:13:53.266 --> 00:13:55.110
Just a little something
to brighten your day.

196
00:13:55.570 --> 00:13:57.951
We think. you looking
kind of pale lately.

197
00:14:06.092 --> 00:14:07.550
Paper cut.

198
00:14:31.204 --> 00:14:32.549
Jas... Jas!

199
00:14:32.817 --> 00:14:34.929
It's okay.
It's just a little...

200
00:14:36.427 --> 00:14:37.923
...blood.

201
00:14:43.876 --> 00:14:45.719
Get Jasper out of here.

202
00:14:51.172 --> 00:14:53.398
I'm sor...
I'm sorry. I can't.

203
00:14:55.702 --> 00:14:57.929
I'll have to stitch this up
in my office.

204
00:15:00.387 --> 00:15:02.078
Check on Jasper.

205
00:15:02.767 --> 00:15:04.265
I'm sure. he's very upset with himself.

206
00:15:04.304 --> 00:15:06.800
And I doubt he'll listen to anyone
but you right now.

207
00:15:07.837 --> 00:15:09.295
Edward?

208
00:15:19.779 --> 00:15:23.350
I never wanted that party.
- It's not your fault.

209
00:15:25.076 --> 00:15:28.342
Jasper hasn't been away from human blood
as long as the rest of us.

210
00:15:29.954 --> 00:15:31.490
How do you do it?

211
00:15:32.411 --> 00:15:34.639
Years and years of practice.

212
00:15:35.023 --> 00:15:36.865
Did you ever think it of...

213
00:15:37.403 --> 00:15:39.247
...just doing it the easier way?

214
00:15:40.244 --> 00:15:41.358
No.

215
00:15:42.588 --> 00:15:44.431
I knew who I wanted to be.

216
00:15:44.545 --> 00:15:46.389
I wanted to help people.

217
00:15:46.926 --> 00:15:48.117
Brings me happiness.

218
00:15:48.462 --> 00:15:50.536
Even if I'm damned about this.

219
00:15:52.610 --> 00:15:54.067
Damned?

220
00:15:54.606 --> 00:15:57.601
Like... like hell?

221
00:16:03.514 --> 00:16:05.357
Carlisle. you can't be damned.

222
00:16:06.048 --> 00:16:08.505
You couldn't. it's impossible.

223
00:16:09.043 --> 00:16:10.503
Thank you. Bella.

224
00:16:10.734 --> 00:16:12.615
You always been very...

225
00:16:13.305 --> 00:16:14.880
...gracious about us.

226
00:16:18.413 --> 00:16:19.911
So. that's it?

227
00:16:20.179 --> 00:16:21.984
That's why he won't change me?

228
00:16:24.557 --> 00:16:26.784
Imagine the situation in reverse.

229
00:16:28.626 --> 00:16:30.777
If you believed as Edward does...

230
00:16:32.467 --> 00:16:34.540
...would you take away his soul?

231
00:16:56.849 --> 00:16:59.000
You can't protect me.

232
00:17:00.805 --> 00:17:02.264
From everything.

233
00:17:02.725 --> 00:17:05.298
At some point.
something's gonna separate us.

234
00:17:07.178 --> 00:17:08.792
It's gonna be an accident.

235
00:17:08.907 --> 00:17:10.482
...or illness.

236
00:17:10.827 --> 00:17:12.631
...or old age.

237
00:17:13.937 --> 00:17:15.704
As long as I'm human.

238
00:17:16.547 --> 00:17:19.159
And the only solution
is to change me.

239
00:17:20.157 --> 00:17:22.961
That's not a solution.
it's a tragedy.

240
00:17:23.076 --> 00:17:25.687
You're not gonna love me
when I look like a grandmother.

241
00:17:35.248 --> 00:17:40.278
Bella. do you not understand
my feelings for you? No?

242
00:17:42.275 --> 00:17:44.118
Carlisle told me...

243
00:17:47.036 --> 00:17:48.880
...how you feel about your soul.

244
00:17:50.569 --> 00:17:52.413
I don't believe that.

245
00:17:53.412 --> 00:17:55.253
So don't worry about mine.

246
00:17:56.636 --> 00:17:58.479
You should go inside.

247
00:18:12.379 --> 00:18:14.222
It's still my birthday.

248
00:18:17.678 --> 00:18:19.522
Can I ask one thing?

249
00:18:23.131 --> 00:18:24.589
Kiss me?

250
00:18:54.387 --> 00:18:56.077
I love you.

251
00:18:58.227 --> 00:18:59.993
I love you.

252
00:20:18.135 --> 00:20:19.325
Hi.

253
00:20:23.164 --> 00:20:25.393
Come for a walk with me.

254
00:20:48.125 --> 00:20:49.967
We got to leave Forks.

255
00:20:53.154 --> 00:20:54.729
Why?

256
00:20:57.762 --> 00:21:00.641
Carlisle's supposed to be
ten years older than he looks.

257
00:21:01.103 --> 00:21:03.059
People are starting to notice.

258
00:21:06.018 --> 00:21:07.475
Okay. I...

259
00:21:08.053 --> 00:21:10.472
I gotta think of something
to say to Charlie.

260
00:21:21.261 --> 00:21:22.835
When you say "we"...

261
00:21:27.061 --> 00:21:29.172
I mean to my family and myself.

262
00:21:33.051 --> 00:21:35.162
Edward. what happened with Jasper.

263
00:21:35.969 --> 00:21:38.158
...it's nothing.
- You're right.

264
00:21:38.734 --> 00:21:40.575
It was nothing.

265
00:21:42.035 --> 00:21:44.263
Nothing the way
I always expected.

266
00:21:46.411 --> 00:21:49.139
And nothing compared to
what could have happened.

267
00:21:55.320 --> 00:21:57.664
You just don't belong
to my world. Bella.

268
00:22:02.732 --> 00:22:04.576
I belong with you.

269
00:22:06.150 --> 00:22:09.029
No. you don't.

270
00:22:10.719 --> 00:22:12.294
I'm coming.

271
00:22:13.137 --> 00:22:14.597
Bella.

272
00:22:15.825 --> 00:22:18.706
I don't want you to come.

273
00:22:25.348 --> 00:22:27.460
You don't want me?

274
00:22:32.490 --> 00:22:33.950
No.

275
00:22:37.214 --> 00:22:39.057
This changes things.

276
00:22:39.863 --> 00:22:41.323
alright.

277
00:22:41.821 --> 00:22:44.049
But if it's not
too much to ask...

278
00:22:45.815 --> 00:22:47.927
...can you at least
promise me something?

279
00:22:50.423 --> 00:22:52.535
Don't do anything reckless.

280
00:22:55.300 --> 00:22:57.142
For Charlie's sake.

281
00:22:58.257 --> 00:23:00.598
And I'll promise something
to you in return.

282
00:23:01.137 --> 00:23:03.363
This is the last time
you'll ever see me.

283
00:23:04.516 --> 00:23:05.973
I won't come back.

284
00:23:06.281 --> 00:23:07.701
And you can go on
with your life...

285
00:23:07.780 --> 00:23:09.890
...without any interference from me.

286
00:23:10.927 --> 00:23:12.387
It will be like...

287
00:23:13.040 --> 00:23:15.266
I never existed.
I promise.

288
00:23:17.877 --> 00:23:20.143
If this is about my soul. take it.

289
00:23:20.220 --> 00:23:23.215
I don't want without you.
- It's not about your soul.

290
00:23:26.517 --> 00:23:29.244
You're just not good for me.

291
00:23:30.319 --> 00:23:32.432
I'm not good enough for you?

292
00:23:33.430 --> 00:23:36.309
I'm just sorry.
I let this go on for so long.

293
00:23:37.615 --> 00:23:39.458
Please...

294
00:23:40.493 --> 00:23:42.339
...don't.

295
00:23:46.831 --> 00:23:48.288
Goodbye.

296
00:24:03.150 --> 00:24:04.609
Edward?

297
00:24:16.589 --> 00:24:18.048
Edward!

298
00:24:25.919 --> 00:24:27.379
Edward!

299
00:26:26.759 --> 00:26:28.605
I'll try to call Cullens place again.

300
00:26:30.063 --> 00:26:32.942
The Cullens left town. Charlie.
- Good riddance!

301
00:26:33.249 --> 00:26:34.824
Where did they go?

302
00:26:35.862 --> 00:26:38.586
We'll find her. Charlie.
- Thanks. Harry.

303
00:26:39.355 --> 00:26:40.853
Charlie?

304
00:26:44.347 --> 00:26:45.920
She's alright.

305
00:26:46.766 --> 00:26:47.955
I got her.

306
00:26:49.108 --> 00:26:50.682
Thank you. Sam.

307
00:27:57.304 --> 00:27:58.763
<i>Alice.</i>

308
00:27:59.531 --> 00:28:01.374
<i>...you have disappeared.</i>

309
00:28:02.986 --> 00:28:04.830
<i>Like everything else.</i>

310
00:28:06.213 --> 00:28:08.554
<i>But who else can I talk to?
I'm lost.</i>

311
00:28:15.389 --> 00:28:17.232
<i>When you left...</i>

312
00:28:18.768 --> 00:28:20.880
<i>and he left...</i>

313
00:28:22.646 --> 00:28:24.759
<i>You took everything with you.</i>

314
00:28:26.832 --> 00:28:29.712
<i>But the absence of him
is everywhere I look...</i>

315
00:28:36.893 --> 00:28:38.237
<i>It's like a huge hole...</i>

316
00:28:38.391 --> 00:28:40.233
<i>...has been punched through my chest.</i>

317
00:29:02.197 --> 00:29:04.309
<i>But in a way I'm glad.</i>

318
00:29:04.808 --> 00:29:07.420
<i>The pain is my only reminder that
he was real...</i>

319
00:29:07.918 --> 00:29:09.378
<i>...that you all were.</i>

320
00:29:17.787 --> 00:29:20.283
alright. that's it.

321
00:29:22.356 --> 00:29:23.547
What?

322
00:29:23.815 --> 00:29:26.810
You're going to Jacksonville
to live with your mother.

323
00:29:29.191 --> 00:29:31.034
I'm not leaving Forks.

324
00:29:32.302 --> 00:29:33.760
Bells...

325
00:29:35.220 --> 00:29:37.024
...he's not coming back.

326
00:29:39.136 --> 00:29:40.596
I know.

327
00:29:41.670 --> 00:29:44.550
It's just not normal.
this behavior.

328
00:29:44.819 --> 00:29:47.047
Quite frankly. it's scaring
the hell outta me.

329
00:29:47.200 --> 00:29:48.698
...and you Mother.

330
00:29:50.002 --> 00:29:52.423
Baby. I... I don't want you to leave.

331
00:29:52.575 --> 00:29:53.266
I don't.

332
00:29:53.343 --> 00:29:55.226
But... just go...

333
00:29:55.265 --> 00:29:57.145
Go to Jacksonville.
make some new friends...

334
00:29:57.222 --> 00:30:00.485
I like my old friends.
- Well. you never see them anymore.

335
00:30:00.562 --> 00:30:02.406
I do. yeah.

336
00:30:04.057 --> 00:30:05.516
I'm...

337
00:30:06.744 --> 00:30:09.739
...gonna go shopping tomorrow.
with Jessica.

338
00:30:10.738 --> 00:30:12.313
You hate shopping.

339
00:30:12.428 --> 00:30:13.619
I...

340
00:30:14.462 --> 00:30:17.188
I need a girl's night out.

341
00:30:19.224 --> 00:30:22.335
alright.
Girl's night.

342
00:30:23.293 --> 00:30:24.754
Shopping.

343
00:30:25.483 --> 00:30:27.595
I like it. go.

344
00:30:27.786 --> 00:30:29.631
Buy some good stuff.

345
00:30:37.002 --> 00:30:39.230
<i>Hi. Jessica. it's Bella.</i>

346
00:30:39.844 --> 00:30:41.956
<i>Oh. yeah. Bella Swan.</i>

347
00:30:46.871 --> 00:30:49.521
I don't know. why you wanna sit through
all those zombies eating people.

348
00:30:49.560 --> 00:30:52.784
...and no hot guys kissing anybody.
It's gross.

349
00:30:52.861 --> 00:30:54.973
Like why there are
so many zombie movies anyway?

350
00:30:55.050 --> 00:30:57.276
Is it supposed to like
draw a parallel with leprosy?

351
00:30:57.354 --> 00:31:00.234
My cousin had leprosy.
it's not funny. you know?

352
00:31:00.311 --> 00:31:03.190
And like is it supposed to be
a metaphor for consumerism?

353
00:31:03.267 --> 00:31:05.110
Because don't be so pleased with
your own like...

354
00:31:05.188 --> 00:31:07.682
...self-reverential cleverness. you know?

355
00:31:07.913 --> 00:31:09.487
Like. some girls like to shop.

356
00:31:09.642 --> 00:31:11.215
Not all girls. apparently.

357
00:31:11.332 --> 00:31:13.942
I was surprised
you called at all. you know?

358
00:31:14.250 --> 00:31:17.629
Like. your depression thing.
I'm totally... totally worried.

359
00:31:17.705 --> 00:31:19.509
After a while. it's like.
she's still bumming?

360
00:31:19.548 --> 00:31:21.698
And I'm going through
stuff too. you know?

361
00:31:21.774 --> 00:31:23.619
Like Mike deciding
he wanted to "I just be friends? "

362
00:31:23.696 --> 00:31:25.385
That's hard. you know?

363
00:31:26.345 --> 00:31:27.804
<i>What's up. guys?</i>

364
00:31:28.649 --> 00:31:30.108
<i>Where you going?</i>

365
00:31:37.749 --> 00:31:39.324
<i>Keep walking.</i>

366
00:31:40.745 --> 00:31:42.587
<i>This is dangerous.</i>

367
00:31:51.227 --> 00:31:52.687
Dude. come on.

368
00:31:57.831 --> 00:31:59.676
I think. I know those guys.

369
00:32:03.399 --> 00:32:06.011
Well. they seem great.
Can we go?

370
00:32:06.816 --> 00:32:08.276
I just need to see something.

371
00:32:09.774 --> 00:32:11.231
<i>Hey. girlie!</i>

372
00:32:15.571 --> 00:32:17.799
alright. alright!
We got a taker.

373
00:32:18.683 --> 00:32:20.257
<i>Turn around.</i>

374
00:32:42.450 --> 00:32:43.794
Sorry. I thought
you were somebody else.

375
00:32:43.871 --> 00:32:45.829
That's cool! I'll be whomever
you want to be. honey.

376
00:32:46.483 --> 00:32:49.592
So. what do you say?

377
00:32:53.356 --> 00:32:56.082
<i>You promised me nothing reckless.</i>

378
00:32:59.615 --> 00:33:02.494
You promised. it would as
you never existed.

379
00:33:08.062 --> 00:33:10.482
You lied.
- Say some. babe?

380
00:33:10.712 --> 00:33:12.555
You know what?
Never mind.

381
00:33:28.643 --> 00:33:29.718
Stop!

382
00:33:29.873 --> 00:33:31.447
Stop! Stop!
Stop!

383
00:33:40.855 --> 00:33:43.352
Hey. um. what the hell is
wrong with you?

384
00:33:43.619 --> 00:33:45.732
Just curious.

385
00:33:46.844 --> 00:33:48.419
I thought that I saw something.

386
00:33:49.763 --> 00:33:53.410
You're insane. actually.
Or suicidal.

387
00:33:53.565 --> 00:33:56.177
That homeboy
could have been a psycho.

388
00:33:56.405 --> 00:33:58.365
I was about to end up
in a FBI interview room.

389
00:33:58.403 --> 00:34:00.284
...like some lame TV show.

390
00:34:00.707 --> 00:34:02.549
Oh. that was such a rush.

391
00:34:04.239 --> 00:34:04.815
Awesome!

392
00:34:04.854 --> 00:34:06.697
So. you're an adrenaline junky now?

393
00:34:06.735 --> 00:34:07.888
That's cool!
You can go bungee jumping.

394
00:34:07.927 --> 00:34:11.190
You don't get on the back of some
random loser's motorcycle!

395
00:34:11.344 --> 00:34:12.533
Crazy!

396
00:34:16.719 --> 00:34:19.599
<i>Alice. I saw him.</i>

397
00:34:21.135 --> 00:34:23.861
<i>Maybe I'm crazy now.
but I guess that's okay.</i>

398
00:34:26.049 --> 00:34:28.775
<i>If the rush of danger is
what it takes to see him...</i>

399
00:34:29.391 --> 00:34:31.233
<i>...then that's what I'll find.</i>

400
00:34:35.188 --> 00:34:36.648
Bella!

401
00:34:37.339 --> 00:34:39.681
Where the hell have you been. crazy?

402
00:34:43.560 --> 00:34:46.747
I... brought you something.
- Okay.

403
00:34:47.516 --> 00:34:49.357
It's a little crazy.

404
00:34:53.890 --> 00:34:56.270
Wow. scrap metal!

405
00:34:56.499 --> 00:34:59.649
You shouldn't have.
- I saved them from the junkyard.

406
00:35:01.684 --> 00:35:04.564
I think. they'll probably cost
more to fix than they're worth.

407
00:35:05.563 --> 00:35:06.483
...but then I thought that...

408
00:35:06.638 --> 00:35:08.327
if I had a mechanic-type friend
to help me out.

409
00:35:08.403 --> 00:35:09.671
Huh. me?

410
00:35:09.824 --> 00:35:12.819
Being the mechanic-type friend?
- That's right.

411
00:35:13.396 --> 00:35:16.658
Since when are you into motorcycles?
- Since now.

412
00:35:21.381 --> 00:35:25.145
I get it if you think this is
really stupid and reckless.

413
00:35:25.222 --> 00:35:28.216
Yeah. it's completely
stupid and reckless.

414
00:35:31.020 --> 00:35:32.479
When do we start?

415
00:35:36.704 --> 00:35:40.659
Now. Please.
- alright.

416
00:35:42.577 --> 00:35:44.919
Oh. hey. be careful.
These things are actually really...

417
00:35:44.996 --> 00:35:46.456
...heavy. So.

418
00:35:51.908 --> 00:35:54.135
Jacob. you're like buff.

419
00:35:54.250 --> 00:35:56.862
How that can happen?
You're like 16. I don't get it.

420
00:35:57.131 --> 00:36:00.010
Age is just a number. baby.
What. you're like 40. now?

421
00:36:03.773 --> 00:36:05.617
Feels like that sometimes.

422
00:36:15.678 --> 00:36:18.097
That song was good.
You don't like it?

423
00:36:19.672 --> 00:36:21.129
I don't really like...

424
00:36:21.821 --> 00:36:24.049
...music anymore kind of...

425
00:36:24.355 --> 00:36:27.043
Okay.
No more music.

426
00:36:30.000 --> 00:36:31.843
I was thinking.
if we're gonna do this everyday.

427
00:36:32.074 --> 00:36:33.533
...and hopefully we will...

428
00:36:33.686 --> 00:36:36.221
We have to. like. fit some homework
in there somewhere.

429
00:36:36.259 --> 00:36:39.101
I don't want Billy thinking that
I'm a bad influence on you.

430
00:36:39.331 --> 00:36:42.825
You influence me?
Please.

431
00:36:44.475 --> 00:36:46.972
Are you...?
I'm older than you.

432
00:36:47.048 --> 00:36:50.428
So that makes me the influencer
and you the influence.

433
00:36:50.504 --> 00:36:51.964
No. no. no.

434
00:36:52.118 --> 00:36:55.611
My size and knowledge base actually
makes me older than you.

435
00:36:55.728 --> 00:36:57.955
Because of your gentle paleness
and lack of know-how.

436
00:36:58.147 --> 00:37:00.565
I convinced you to build
two-wheeled death machines with me.

437
00:37:00.642 --> 00:37:02.753
Don't you think that makes
you funny. young and naive?

438
00:37:04.137 --> 00:37:06.364
Okay.
So. where do we stand?

439
00:37:07.132 --> 00:37:08.591
I'm thirty five...

440
00:37:08.974 --> 00:37:10.895
...and you might be like 32.
- Come on.

441
00:37:11.124 --> 00:37:12.852
Yo. Jake. you in there?
- No. it's okay.

442
00:37:12.929 --> 00:37:14.466
It's... It's just my boys.

443
00:37:14.620 --> 00:37:17.423
Hey. Jake.
- Hey. Guys. this is Bella.

444
00:37:17.499 --> 00:37:19.918
Bella. that's Quil and Embry.

445
00:37:20.570 --> 00:37:22.145
I'm Quil Ateara.

446
00:37:24.258 --> 00:37:25.946
So the bike building story is true.

447
00:37:26.062 --> 00:37:28.020
Oh. yeah. yeah!
I taught him everything he knows.

448
00:37:28.212 --> 00:37:30.438
What about the part
where you're his girlfriend?

449
00:37:31.745 --> 00:37:35.124
Uh. we're friends. you know?
- Hmm. Burn!

450
00:37:35.278 --> 00:37:38.695
Actually. I remember. I said
she's a girl and a friend.

451
00:37:39.002 --> 00:37:40.691
Embry. do you remember him
making that distinction?

452
00:37:40.729 --> 00:37:41.537
Nope!

453
00:37:41.652 --> 00:37:44.070
So you guys have girlfriends.
It's awesome.

454
00:37:45.300 --> 00:37:46.337
Yeah. right.

455
00:37:46.528 --> 00:37:48.947
Quil's actually taken his cousin to prom.

456
00:37:49.446 --> 00:37:50.368
Yeah. that's still a riot.

457
00:37:50.445 --> 00:37:52.287
You want funny. Black?
I'll give you funny.

458
00:37:54.746 --> 00:37:55.821
Jesus!

459
00:37:57.394 --> 00:38:00.391
I got five bucks on Quil.
- You're on.

460
00:38:22.776 --> 00:38:26.041
<i>Dear Alice. I wish.
I had your real address.</i>

461
00:38:26.807 --> 00:38:28.920
<i>I wish. I could tell you
about Jake.</i>

462
00:38:29.611 --> 00:38:31.455
<i>He makes me feel better.</i>

463
00:38:32.837 --> 00:38:35.563
<i>I mean.
he makes me feel alive.</i>

464
00:38:37.599 --> 00:38:39.440
<i>The hole in my chest...</i>

465
00:38:40.364 --> 00:38:42.206
<i>...while when I'm with Jake.</i>

466
00:38:43.434 --> 00:38:46.814
<i>It's like. it almost healed.
For a while.</i>

467
00:38:47.505 --> 00:38:49.194
Quil keeps asking to come over.

468
00:38:49.425 --> 00:38:51.537
I think he likes you
a little too much.

469
00:38:53.456 --> 00:38:56.183
Oh. I'm really not into
the whole cougar thing. you know?

470
00:38:59.293 --> 00:39:01.138
What's up with you and age?

471
00:39:01.636 --> 00:39:04.055
I mean. how old was that
Cullen guy anyway?

472
00:39:06.934 --> 00:39:09.355
<i>But even Jake can't keep
the dreams away.</i>

473
00:39:20.259 --> 00:39:21.448
Hey. Bella!

474
00:39:22.408 --> 00:39:24.752
You're alright. You're okay?
- No.

475
00:39:34.772 --> 00:39:36.463
I thought this thing was
starting to work.

476
00:39:36.541 --> 00:39:39.382
...but I guess not.

477
00:39:45.179 --> 00:39:47.023
Can I ask you something?

478
00:39:48.866 --> 00:39:50.709
Hanging out with Jacob...

479
00:39:51.708 --> 00:39:55.278
...does seems to take your mind
off things for a bit. doesn't it?

480
00:40:00.078 --> 00:40:01.921
You know. sometimes...

481
00:40:03.534 --> 00:40:06.528
...you gotta learn to love
what's good for you.

482
00:40:07.412 --> 00:40:09.255
You know. what I mean?

483
00:40:11.598 --> 00:40:13.057
Of course. what do I know?

484
00:40:13.903 --> 00:40:16.205
I'm just a terminal bachelor.

485
00:40:18.279 --> 00:40:20.121
Famous ladies man.

486
00:40:22.811 --> 00:40:24.001
Okay...

487
00:40:25.806 --> 00:40:27.265
Go to bed.

488
00:40:29.337 --> 00:40:30.681
I love you.

489
00:40:36.634 --> 00:40:37.710
If I told you.

490
00:40:38.092 --> 00:40:40.972
...I couldn't have fixed these bikes.
what would you say?

491
00:40:43.278 --> 00:40:45.697
Are you doubting your mad skills?

492
00:40:46.463 --> 00:40:49.958
No. definitely not.
I mean. they're all fine.

493
00:40:50.457 --> 00:40:52.300
It's just...

494
00:40:53.681 --> 00:40:56.947
May be if I was smarter
would have dragged out to rebuild them.

495
00:41:01.093 --> 00:41:02.706
If you told me.
you couldn't fix these bikes.

496
00:41:02.744 --> 00:41:04.587
I would say that that's...

497
00:41:05.164 --> 00:41:07.006
...really too bad but...

498
00:41:07.505 --> 00:41:10.233
...he's gonna find something else to do.

499
00:41:14.763 --> 00:41:16.339
Is that Sam Uley?

500
00:41:17.259 --> 00:41:19.985
Yeah. and his cult.

501
00:41:22.404 --> 00:41:23.596
Oh. my God!

502
00:41:26.782 --> 00:41:28.241
Did you see that?

503
00:41:33.809 --> 00:41:35.920
They're not really fighting. Bella.

504
00:41:36.112 --> 00:41:37.686
They're cliff diving.

505
00:41:37.763 --> 00:41:40.644
Scary as hell.
but a total rush.

506
00:41:43.255 --> 00:41:45.866
Rush?
- Most of us jump from lower down.

507
00:41:45.943 --> 00:41:49.053
We'll leave the showing off
to Sam and his disciples.

508
00:41:51.165 --> 00:41:53.392
Is some kind of beef
with them or something?

509
00:41:55.503 --> 00:41:56.694
Oh. no.

510
00:41:56.963 --> 00:41:58.921
They just think they run this place.

511
00:41:59.804 --> 00:42:02.684
Embry used to call them hall
monitors on steroids.

512
00:42:02.799 --> 00:42:05.295
Now. look at him.
- That's Embry?

513
00:42:06.640 --> 00:42:08.983
Yeah.
- What happened to him?

514
00:42:09.328 --> 00:42:10.902
He missed some school...

515
00:42:11.056 --> 00:42:14.818
...and all of a sudden started following
Sam around like a little puppy.

516
00:42:15.011 --> 00:42:17.122
Same thing with Paul and Jared.

517
00:42:18.159 --> 00:42:20.577
Sam keeps giving me this look.

518
00:42:22.422 --> 00:42:24.840
...like he's waiting for me
or something.

519
00:42:26.145 --> 00:42:28.373
It's kinda starting to freak me out.

520
00:42:29.026 --> 00:42:30.869
Well. you should just avoid him.

521
00:42:33.135 --> 00:42:34.709
I'll try.

522
00:42:50.952 --> 00:42:52.411
Okay.

523
00:42:55.060 --> 00:42:57.480
You look scared.
- I'm not.

524
00:42:58.785 --> 00:43:01.472
Alright! Brake.

525
00:43:04.813 --> 00:43:06.925
Clutch. Good.

526
00:43:07.884 --> 00:43:09.345
Gas.

527
00:43:11.533 --> 00:43:12.992
Ready?

528
00:43:13.607 --> 00:43:16.870
Now slowly... release the clutch.

529
00:43:18.751 --> 00:43:20.212
<i>Bella.</i>

530
00:43:23.206 --> 00:43:24.665
<i>Stop.</i>

531
00:43:29.120 --> 00:43:30.962
You alright?

532
00:43:31.885 --> 00:43:33.459
I'm gonna go again.

533
00:43:53.310 --> 00:43:54.885
Hit the brake!

534
00:44:08.669 --> 00:44:11.397
I wanna go again.
- Are you trying to get yourself killed?

535
00:44:11.626 --> 00:44:13.893
I'll try again.
- No. forget it.

536
00:44:14.659 --> 00:44:16.234
No more bikes.

537
00:44:17.156 --> 00:44:18.731
Man. your head.

538
00:44:22.340 --> 00:44:23.799
Oh. my God. I'm sorry.

539
00:44:24.759 --> 00:44:27.369
You're apologizing for bleeding?

540
00:44:29.635 --> 00:44:31.479
Yeah. I guess. I am.

541
00:44:32.170 --> 00:44:35.318
It's just blood. Bella.
No big deal.

542
00:44:47.529 --> 00:44:49.373
What are you staring at?

543
00:44:52.828 --> 00:44:54.671
You're sort of beautiful.

544
00:45:02.274 --> 00:45:04.502
How hard did you hit your head?

545
00:45:05.882 --> 00:45:07.074
I don't know.

546
00:45:09.339 --> 00:45:10.530
Let's go.

547
00:45:14.100 --> 00:45:17.211
I did see something in the woods.
- Sure. baby. I believe you.

548
00:45:17.288 --> 00:45:19.706
No. he doesn't.
He's just trying to get lucky.

549
00:45:22.126 --> 00:45:24.546
It was jet black and huge.

550
00:45:24.659 --> 00:45:27.003
On all fours. it was still taller
than a person.

551
00:45:27.464 --> 00:45:28.538
A bear. may be?

552
00:45:28.615 --> 00:45:30.727
Or an alien.
You're lucky that you didn't get probed.

553
00:45:30.842 --> 00:45:32.033
Oh. yeah.

554
00:45:32.379 --> 00:45:34.605
Well. I saw it.

555
00:45:34.876 --> 00:45:36.717
You're not the only one.

556
00:45:37.754 --> 00:45:39.866
My Dad's been getting reports
at the station.

557
00:45:40.251 --> 00:45:42.977
Like five hikers been killed by some bear.

558
00:45:43.246 --> 00:45:44.818
But they can't find the bear.

559
00:45:48.275 --> 00:45:50.503
Last time you clowns
doubt my girlfriend.

560
00:45:54.881 --> 00:45:56.339
So. I mean...

561
00:45:57.069 --> 00:45:58.642
Bella is back.

562
00:46:02.098 --> 00:46:06.093
Yeah. I guess so.
- Huh. that's... Welcome.

563
00:46:07.475 --> 00:46:11.238
So listen. not now that...
You know. you're talking and...

564
00:46:11.699 --> 00:46:13.925
...eating again. you know?

565
00:46:14.118 --> 00:46:16.730
You gotta get that protein in there.

566
00:46:18.227 --> 00:46:22.104
I was just wondering.
if you wanted to go see a movie with me.

567
00:46:26.328 --> 00:46:29.322
Yeah. sure.
Yeah. I do.

568
00:46:30.437 --> 00:46:32.280
Cool. um. let me see...

569
00:46:32.318 --> 00:46:36.734
We could check out
"Love spelled backwards is love. "

570
00:46:37.004 --> 00:46:39.999
Yeah. it's a dumb title.
but. um. it's a romantic comedy.

571
00:46:40.037 --> 00:46:42.917
I mean. it's supposed to be.
- No. No romance.

572
00:46:46.602 --> 00:46:49.713
How about "Face Punch"?
You heard of that?

573
00:46:51.173 --> 00:46:54.437
Well. it's an action movie.
- Yeah. it's perfect.

574
00:46:55.472 --> 00:46:57.316
With guns... adrenaline...

575
00:46:58.046 --> 00:47:00.273
...it's my thing
- Okay.

576
00:47:00.657 --> 00:47:03.536
We should get a bunch of people to go.
Do you guys wanna go see...

577
00:47:04.228 --> 00:47:05.956
..."Face Punch"?
- "Face Punch"? Yeah!

578
00:47:05.995 --> 00:47:07.530
Mike. hey. we were supposed
to watch that?

579
00:47:07.607 --> 00:47:09.257
Remember the trailer's like...
- Yeah?

580
00:47:09.295 --> 00:47:11.331
Punch his face in.
- I don't remember that.

581
00:47:12.368 --> 00:47:14.249
Movie night with Bella!

582
00:47:17.090 --> 00:47:20.854
So. "Face Punch". huh?
You like action movies?

583
00:47:22.352 --> 00:47:23.927
Not really.

584
00:47:26.652 --> 00:47:29.648
I heard it sucks. Bad.

585
00:47:30.568 --> 00:47:33.680
Hey. are you even old enough
to see this movie?

586
00:47:34.446 --> 00:47:36.675
I mean. you know. without adult supervision?
- Right. yeah.

587
00:47:36.753 --> 00:47:39.747
Well. she's buying my ticket for me.
- She's buying it. okay.

588
00:47:41.013 --> 00:47:43.893
Jessica bailed
and Angela's got the stomach flu

589
00:47:43.932 --> 00:47:45.774
...so Eric's taking care of her.

590
00:47:47.081 --> 00:47:49.191
So. it's just us three.
- Great.

591
00:47:50.152 --> 00:47:51.996
Great.
- Yeah.

592
00:47:54.913 --> 00:47:55.720
<i>Put the gun down.</i>

593
00:47:55.874 --> 00:47:58.676
<i>Put your gun down or I'm gonna
blow your freaking head off.</i>

594
00:47:58.714 --> 00:47:59.483
<i>Both of you!</i>

595
00:47:59.521 --> 00:48:03.669
<i>Put both of your guns down or I'm gonna
blow both of your freaking heads off.</i>

596
00:48:05.549 --> 00:48:07.394
<i>Alright. let's do this!</i>

597
00:48:24.212 --> 00:48:26.055
Okay. I think I'm gonna throw up!

598
00:48:32.353 --> 00:48:35.846
Jesus!
- What a marshmallow!

599
00:48:36.846 --> 00:48:39.724
You should hold out for someone
with a stronger stomach.

600
00:48:40.108 --> 00:48:43.296
Someone who laughs at the gore
that makes weaker men vomit.

601
00:48:43.488 --> 00:48:45.907
Yeah. I'll keep my eye open for that.

602
00:48:47.443 --> 00:48:49.786
I feel bad.
He probably has that flu that's...

603
00:48:49.976 --> 00:48:52.051
...going around.

604
00:48:54.892 --> 00:48:59.039
What? I can't hold your hand?
- No. of course. you can.

605
00:49:01.996 --> 00:49:04.722
I just think it means
something really different to you.

606
00:49:04.799 --> 00:49:05.875
So...

607
00:49:07.793 --> 00:49:11.172
Okay. tell me something.
You like me. right?

608
00:49:15.742 --> 00:49:18.468
And you think. I'm sorta beautiful?

609
00:49:19.199 --> 00:49:23.346
Jake. please...
don't do this.

610
00:49:29.336 --> 00:49:30.796
Why?

611
00:49:33.866 --> 00:49:35.710
Because you are about
to ruin everything.

612
00:49:38.205 --> 00:49:41.470
And I need you.

613
00:49:47.267 --> 00:49:49.110
Well. I've got loads of time.

614
00:49:50.800 --> 00:49:52.643
I'm not gonna give up.

615
00:49:53.718 --> 00:49:55.561
I don't want you to.

616
00:49:55.753 --> 00:49:57.212
But...

617
00:49:58.326 --> 00:50:00.784
It's just because I don't want you
to go anywhere.

618
00:50:04.240 --> 00:50:06.044
It's... it's really selfish.

619
00:50:09.462 --> 00:50:12.572
You know. I'm not like a car
that you can fix up.

620
00:50:16.604 --> 00:50:18.293
I'm never gonna run right.

621
00:50:18.602 --> 00:50:20.444
So I should be fair to you.

622
00:50:22.747 --> 00:50:24.591
It's because of him. right?

623
00:50:34.727 --> 00:50:39.643
Look. I know what he did to you.

624
00:50:41.103 --> 00:50:46.133
But. Bella. I would never.
ever do that.

625
00:50:47.707 --> 00:50:51.086
I won't ever hurt you.
I promise.

626
00:50:52.276 --> 00:50:54.388
I won't let you down.

627
00:50:55.042 --> 00:50:56.883
You can count on me.

628
00:51:04.526 --> 00:51:06.368
Well...

629
00:51:10.669 --> 00:51:12.512
I need to go home.

630
00:51:18.810 --> 00:51:22.458
I'm... I was feeling sick
before the movie. okay?

631
00:51:24.992 --> 00:51:27.104
What is your problem?
- Right now?

632
00:51:27.181 --> 00:51:28.639
You are my problem.

633
00:51:28.947 --> 00:51:32.326
Feeling sick?
Maybe you need to go to the hospital.

634
00:51:33.400 --> 00:51:35.092
Do you want me
to put you in the hospital?

635
00:51:35.244 --> 00:51:38.355
Jake... Jake. the movie's over.
What are you doing?

636
00:51:38.853 --> 00:51:42.233
Jake. you're really hot.

637
00:51:42.886 --> 00:51:45.881
Like. you feel like you have a fever.
Are you okay?

638
00:51:46.918 --> 00:51:48.759
I don't know what's happening.

639
00:51:51.103 --> 00:51:52.678
I gotta go.

640
00:51:57.515 --> 00:51:59.358
That dude is weird.

641
00:52:02.583 --> 00:52:03.505
<i>Jake.</i>

642
00:52:03.659 --> 00:52:05.502
<i>Uh. your Dad says you have mono.</i>

643
00:52:05.656 --> 00:52:09.151
<i>He won't let me visit but...
would you call me?</i>

644
00:52:14.104 --> 00:52:17.406
<i>Hey. uh. it's me again.
I just...</i>

645
00:52:17.597 --> 00:52:20.018
<i>I'm sorry about what I said
at the movie theatre.</i>

646
00:52:21.629 --> 00:52:25.008
<i>I just wanted to hear your voice.
So. no pressure.</i>

647
00:52:27.389 --> 00:52:31.920
Jacob. please call me.

648
00:52:32.266 --> 00:52:35.261
Okay. we should be
back around three.

649
00:52:41.365 --> 00:52:42.595
Hey!

650
00:52:43.364 --> 00:52:47.011
Look. I don't have to go fishing today.
- Yes. you do.

651
00:52:47.202 --> 00:52:49.814
Yeah. you do. Go.
What are you talking about?

652
00:52:49.967 --> 00:52:52.848
Just be careful.
- I always am.

653
00:52:54.306 --> 00:52:56.648
Those bears won't get
the drop on me. Bella.

654
00:52:56.802 --> 00:52:59.030
My kung foo is strong.

655
00:53:30.708 --> 00:53:32.283
Jake!

656
00:53:38.772 --> 00:53:40.616
You cut your hair?

657
00:53:43.303 --> 00:53:45.529
And got a tattoo?

658
00:53:48.103 --> 00:53:49.293
Bella...

659
00:53:49.484 --> 00:53:51.904
I thought you were too sick
to come outside.

660
00:53:53.248 --> 00:53:56.244
Or pick up the phone
when I'd call.

661
00:53:56.973 --> 00:54:00.736
Go away.
- What?

662
00:54:02.349 --> 00:54:03.924
Go away.

663
00:54:05.382 --> 00:54:07.610
What happened to you?
What's wrong?

664
00:54:07.686 --> 00:54:10.297
Hey. what happened?

665
00:54:12.678 --> 00:54:15.557
Did Sam get to you?
Is that what's happening?

666
00:54:15.712 --> 00:54:19.590
Sam's trying to help me.
don't blame him.

667
00:54:19.936 --> 00:54:21.778
But if you want somebody to blame.

668
00:54:22.277 --> 00:54:25.041
How about those
filthy bloodsuckers. you love?

669
00:54:25.158 --> 00:54:27.000
The Cullens.

670
00:54:33.029 --> 00:54:34.296
I don't know
what are you talking abØut.

671
00:54:34.372 --> 00:54:36.715
You know exactly
what I'm talking about.

672
00:54:36.985 --> 00:54:40.247
You been lying to everyone.
Charlie...

673
00:54:41.784 --> 00:54:43.627
But you can't lie to me.

674
00:54:44.779 --> 00:54:48.926
Not anymore. Bella.
- Come on! Jacob!

675
00:54:54.456 --> 00:54:56.299
Look. Bella...

676
00:54:57.067 --> 00:54:59.294
We can't be friends anymore.

677
00:55:00.176 --> 00:55:02.289
Jake. I know that
I have been...

678
00:55:03.249 --> 00:55:04.709
...hurting you.

679
00:55:05.591 --> 00:55:09.163
It's... it's killing me.
It kills me.

680
00:55:10.736 --> 00:55:13.885
If you. may be.
give me like some time.

681
00:55:14.038 --> 00:55:15.497
Don't!

682
00:55:16.342 --> 00:55:17.917
It's not you.

683
00:55:20.528 --> 00:55:23.793
It's not you. it's me. right?
Really?

684
00:55:24.176 --> 00:55:27.056
It's true!
It is me.

685
00:55:29.090 --> 00:55:32.086
I'm not good.

686
00:55:33.929 --> 00:55:37.078
I used to be... a great kid.

687
00:55:38.384 --> 00:55:39.918
Not anymore.

688
00:55:40.764 --> 00:55:44.450
It doesn't even matter. alright?
This is over.

689
00:55:44.604 --> 00:55:46.754
You can't break up with me.

690
00:55:48.675 --> 00:55:50.517
I mean...

691
00:55:51.208 --> 00:55:53.052
I mean. you're my best friend.

692
00:55:55.587 --> 00:55:57.428
You promised me.

693
00:55:58.658 --> 00:56:00.116
I know.

694
00:56:00.885 --> 00:56:03.227
I promised that
I won't hurt you. Bella.

695
00:56:04.264 --> 00:56:06.721
And this is me keeping that promise.

696
00:56:07.336 --> 00:56:09.178
Go home.

697
00:56:09.332 --> 00:56:13.479
And don't come back.
Ør you're gonna get hurt.

698
00:56:25.921 --> 00:56:27.573
<i>Alice...</i>

699
00:56:27.878 --> 00:56:29.338
<i>Things are...</i>

700
00:56:30.990 --> 00:56:32.794
<i>Things are bad again.</i>

701
00:56:34.061 --> 00:56:37.939
<i>Without Jake. I just...
I can't stand it.</i>

702
00:56:40.205 --> 00:56:42.432
<i>I don't see Edward anymore.</i>

703
00:56:43.969 --> 00:56:46.694
<i>Now it really feels like
he never existed.</i>

704
00:56:53.798 --> 00:56:57.023
<i>I will find a place
where I can see him again.</i>

705
00:57:49.859 --> 00:57:53.085
Bella.
- Laurent!

706
00:57:55.006 --> 00:57:57.193
I didn't expect to find you here.

707
00:57:59.537 --> 00:58:04.220
I went to visit the Cullens. but...
the house is empty.

708
00:58:05.756 --> 00:58:07.983
I'm surprised they left you behind.

709
00:58:08.369 --> 00:58:10.210
Weren't you sort of a. um.

710
00:58:11.515 --> 00:58:13.360
...a pet of theirs?

711
00:58:13.821 --> 00:58:15.587
Yeah. You could say that.

712
00:58:15.664 --> 00:58:18.428
Do they Cullens visit often?

713
00:58:22.882 --> 00:58:24.341
<i>Lie.</i>

714
00:58:29.026 --> 00:58:31.637
Yeah. absolutely. all the time.
- Lie better.

715
00:58:31.945 --> 00:58:34.401
I'll tell them that you stopped by.

716
00:58:35.247 --> 00:58:38.319
I probably shouldn't tell...

717
00:58:39.394 --> 00:58:41.006
...to Edward.

718
00:58:41.852 --> 00:58:46.382
Because he's pretty protective.
- But he's far away. isn't he?

719
00:58:47.995 --> 00:58:49.685
Why are you here?

720
00:58:49.838 --> 00:58:54.676
I came as a favor to Victoria.

721
00:58:57.134 --> 00:58:58.284
Victoria?

722
00:58:58.362 --> 00:59:00.091
She asked me to see
if you were still...

723
00:59:00.168 --> 00:59:02.280
...under the protection
of the Cullens.

724
00:59:02.664 --> 00:59:05.966
Victoria feels it's only fair
to kill Edwards mate...

725
00:59:06.349 --> 00:59:07.885
...given he killed hers.

726
00:59:08.040 --> 00:59:09.881
An eye for an eye.

727
00:59:10.420 --> 00:59:13.337
Threaten him.
- Edward would know who did it!

728
00:59:13.569 --> 00:59:15.181
And he'd come after you.

729
00:59:15.795 --> 00:59:17.947
I don't think he will.

730
00:59:18.867 --> 00:59:21.478
After all. how much could
you mean to him...

731
00:59:22.169 --> 00:59:25.165
...if he left you here unprØtected?

732
00:59:26.623 --> 00:59:29.620
Victoria won't be happy
about me killing you.

733
00:59:29.850 --> 00:59:32.000
But I can't help myself.

734
00:59:32.153 --> 00:59:34.917
You're so mouthwatering.
- Please. don't!

735
00:59:35.302 --> 00:59:38.296
I mean. you'd helped us.
- Shhhh!

736
00:59:38.605 --> 00:59:41.753
Don't be afraid.
I'm doing you a kindness.

737
00:59:41.906 --> 00:59:47.360
Victoria plans on killing you
slowly. painfully.

738
00:59:47.819 --> 00:59:51.967
...where as I'll make it quick.
I promise.

739
00:59:52.735 --> 00:59:54.808
You will feel nothing.

740
01:00:00.030 --> 01:00:01.874
Edward. I love you.

741
01:00:03.870 --> 01:00:06.251
I don't believe it.

742
01:01:09.839 --> 01:01:11.528
Dad. I saw them!

743
01:01:11.605 --> 01:01:14.370
What's the matter?
- In the woods. They are not bears!

744
01:01:14.485 --> 01:01:15.292
What you mean in the woods?

745
01:01:15.330 --> 01:01:17.174
Bella. what the hell were you doing
out in the woods?

746
01:01:17.250 --> 01:01:20.744
They are wolves.
I mean. they're like huge wolves!

747
01:01:20.822 --> 01:01:23.892
Are you sure about that. Bella?
- Yeah. I just saw them.

748
01:01:24.046 --> 01:01:26.427
They were after... something.

749
01:01:26.735 --> 01:01:30.152
Wolves? You saw?

750
01:01:33.032 --> 01:01:35.835
Alright.
Well. Harry.

751
01:01:36.679 --> 01:01:37.754
...feel like going hunting?

752
01:01:37.869 --> 01:01:39.483
Can you get some of
your guys together?

753
01:01:40.250 --> 01:01:42.861
Sure. yeah. I'll...
I'll just...

754
01:01:44.089 --> 01:01:46.317
<i>I know that those wolves
will be dead.</i>

755
01:01:47.239 --> 01:01:49.466
<i>And Laurent would have told her
I'm unprotected.</i>

756
01:01:50.465 --> 01:01:52.001
<i>Victoria.</i>

757
01:01:53.152 --> 01:01:54.767
I should go to the station.

758
01:01:54.920 --> 01:01:56.992
Dad. you should...
You should go.

759
01:01:57.453 --> 01:01:59.680
You can just stay in the house?

760
01:02:24.025 --> 01:02:25.714
Bella!

761
01:02:27.557 --> 01:02:28.787
Oh. you scared me.

762
01:02:29.016 --> 01:02:31.935
What the hell are you doing?
- Back up. I'm coming up.

763
01:02:47.370 --> 01:02:49.444
Look. look. I'm sorry.

764
01:02:55.664 --> 01:02:58.045
For what?
- I wish I could explain.

765
01:02:58.122 --> 01:03:01.502
...but I literally... can't!

766
01:03:09.564 --> 01:03:12.791
Have you ever had a secret
you couldn't tell anyone?

767
01:03:13.636 --> 01:03:15.862
One that wasn't yours to share.

768
01:03:18.857 --> 01:03:20.663
Well. that's what
it's like for me.

769
01:03:21.468 --> 01:03:22.928
Or worse.

770
01:03:24.081 --> 01:03:28.227
You have no idea.
how tight I'm bounded.

771
01:03:28.380 --> 01:03:29.995
I hate this.

772
01:03:30.760 --> 01:03:32.682
I hate what they have
done to you.

773
01:03:46.352 --> 01:03:49.116
I mean. the killer part is
you already know!

774
01:03:53.341 --> 01:03:58.408
Bella. do you remember.
when walked on the beach in La Push?

775
01:03:59.330 --> 01:04:01.712
The sto...

776
01:04:04.476 --> 01:04:09.159
The story...
The story about the cold ones.

777
01:04:11.464 --> 01:04:14.765
I guees. I understand why that's
the only part you remember.

778
01:04:21.755 --> 01:04:25.595
There must gotta be something
You can do...

779
01:04:25.672 --> 01:04:27.899
No.
I'm in it for life.

780
01:04:29.051 --> 01:04:31.047
May be we should just
get out of here for a while.

781
01:04:31.584 --> 01:04:34.810
We'll just leave.
Just you and me.

782
01:04:35.423 --> 01:04:37.269
You can do that?

783
01:04:39.955 --> 01:04:41.798
I'll do it for you.

784
01:04:47.866 --> 01:04:51.245
It's not something
I can just run away from. Bella.

785
01:04:52.013 --> 01:04:56.159
But I would run away with you.

786
01:04:59.308 --> 01:05:01.690
If I could.

787
01:05:04.608 --> 01:05:08.062
I gotta go.
They'll certainly wonder where I am.

788
01:05:11.825 --> 01:05:13.286
Come here.

789
01:05:17.509 --> 01:05:21.272
Please...
Try to remember.

790
01:05:22.885 --> 01:05:27.570
It would be so much easier
if you knew...

791
01:05:30.027 --> 01:05:32.946
I tried. but...
Jake.

792
01:05:33.176 --> 01:05:35.787
Jake. what are you doing?
Wait. Jake.

793
01:05:42.545 --> 01:05:44.004
Jake!

794
01:05:59.901 --> 01:06:01.591
Edward. I'm scared.

795
01:06:02.204 --> 01:06:04.049
You should be.

796
01:06:08.694 --> 01:06:10.613
<i>Really it's just like an old story...</i>

797
01:06:10.730 --> 01:06:12.420
<i>That we're not supposed to
say anything about...</i>

798
01:06:12.497 --> 01:06:15.953
<i>Did you know. the Quileute are
supposed to be descendants from wØlves?</i>

799
01:06:30.237 --> 01:06:31.541
Bella.

800
01:06:31.733 --> 01:06:33.155
I need to see him.

801
01:06:34.229 --> 01:06:35.919
He's not in.

802
01:06:37.377 --> 01:06:39.605
I'm sorry. really need to see him.
- Bella?

803
01:06:55.732 --> 01:06:57.192
What did you do?

804
01:06:58.613 --> 01:06:59.533
Okay. what did you do?
- Hey!

805
01:06:59.572 --> 01:07:00.647
What did you do to him?
- Easy!

806
01:07:00.723 --> 01:07:02.798
He didn't want this!
- But we do.

807
01:07:02.874 --> 01:07:04.871
What did he do? What did he tell you?
- Both of you calm...

808
01:07:04.948 --> 01:07:08.097
Nothing! He told me nothing.
because he's scared of you!

809
01:07:13.511 --> 01:07:16.007
Too late. now.
- Bella. get back.

810
01:07:16.353 --> 01:07:19.463
Paul. calm down now.

811
01:07:27.411 --> 01:07:28.832
Bella!

812
01:07:29.908 --> 01:07:31.366
Run!

813
01:07:33.823 --> 01:07:35.551
Jake. run!

814
01:08:12.760 --> 01:08:14.602
Take Bella back to Emily's place.

815
01:08:15.985 --> 01:08:17.829
Guess the wolf's out of the bag.

816
01:08:23.088 --> 01:08:24.279
<i>Alice...</i>

817
01:08:24.626 --> 01:08:27.083
<i>Is it possible that everything is true?</i>

818
01:08:27.274 --> 01:08:29.118
<i>The fairy tales and
horror stories?</i>

819
01:08:29.655 --> 01:08:33.686
<i>Is it possible that there isn't anything
sane and normal at all?</i>

820
01:08:35.262 --> 01:08:36.988
Hey. I think. we should go back
and see if Jacob's okay.

821
01:08:37.104 --> 01:08:39.714
I hope Paul gets some teeth in him.
Serve him right.

822
01:08:39.831 --> 01:08:42.787
No way. Jake's a natural.
You see him phase on the fly?

823
01:08:42.864 --> 01:08:44.707
I gotta fiver says.
Paul doesn't touch him.

824
01:08:45.091 --> 01:08:47.510
Come on in. Bella.
We won't bite.

825
01:08:47.625 --> 01:08:49.469
Speak for yourself.

826
01:08:58.838 --> 01:09:01.487
Oh. hey. about Emily...
Sam's fiance.

827
01:09:01.680 --> 01:09:04.060
...don't stare.
It bugs him.

828
01:09:05.749 --> 01:09:07.286
Why would I stare?

829
01:09:07.363 --> 01:09:11.049
You guys hungry?
Like I have to ask...

830
01:09:17.653 --> 01:09:19.112
Who's this?

831
01:09:19.227 --> 01:09:21.416
Bella Swan.
Who else?

832
01:09:23.566 --> 01:09:26.254
So. youre the vampire girl.

833
01:09:28.635 --> 01:09:31.477
So. you're the wolf girl.

834
01:09:33.473 --> 01:09:34.701
Guess so.

835
01:09:34.933 --> 01:09:37.698
Well. I'm engaged to one.

836
01:09:40.462 --> 01:09:42.266
Save some for your brothers.

837
01:09:42.382 --> 01:09:44.071
And the ladies first.

838
01:09:44.379 --> 01:09:47.220
Muffin?
- Sure. Thanks.

839
01:09:47.297 --> 01:09:50.944
Leave it to Jake upto find
a way around Sam's gag order.

840
01:09:51.136 --> 01:09:54.592
He didn't say anything to me.
- That's a wolf thing.

841
01:09:54.707 --> 01:09:57.049
Alpha's orders get obeyed
whether we want to or not.

842
01:09:57.165 --> 01:09:59.353
Alright. check it out!
We can hear each other's thoughts.

843
01:09:59.431 --> 01:10:02.426
Will you just shut up?
These are trade secrets.

844
01:10:02.579 --> 01:10:05.575
Damn it!
This chick runs with vampires.

845
01:10:06.419 --> 01:10:08.492
I can't really run with vampires.

846
01:10:10.720 --> 01:10:12.564
Because they are fast.

847
01:10:12.832 --> 01:10:16.019
Yeah? Oh. we are faster.

848
01:10:16.940 --> 01:10:18.631
Freaked out yet?

849
01:10:20.089 --> 01:10:22.470
You're not the first monsters. I met.

850
01:10:22.623 --> 01:10:25.349
Jake's right.
You are good with the weird.

851
01:10:46.661 --> 01:10:48.120
Sorry.

852
01:11:01.944 --> 01:11:03.786
So you're a werewolf?

853
01:11:05.400 --> 01:11:08.125
Yeah. last time I checked.

854
01:11:09.738 --> 01:11:13.003
A few lucky members of the tribe
that have the gene.

855
01:11:13.155 --> 01:11:17.381
If a bloodsucker moves into town.
and the fever sets in.

856
01:11:19.376 --> 01:11:20.837
Mono?

857
01:11:22.103 --> 01:11:23.944
Yeah. I wish.

858
01:11:26.557 --> 01:11:30.818
You can't find a way to stop?

859
01:11:32.815 --> 01:11:35.696
I mean it's wrong.

860
01:11:37.424 --> 01:11:39.843
It's not a life-style choice. Bella.

861
01:11:40.188 --> 01:11:42.608
I was born this way.
I can't help it.

862
01:11:43.031 --> 01:11:43.835
You are such a hypocrite.

863
01:11:43.912 --> 01:11:45.871
What. I'm not the
right kind of monster for you?

864
01:11:45.910 --> 01:11:49.902
It's not what you are.
It's what you do.

865
01:11:50.056 --> 01:11:51.901
They never hurt anybody.

866
01:11:53.666 --> 01:11:55.126
You killed people. Jake.

867
01:11:55.203 --> 01:11:58.081
Bella. we're not killing anyone.

868
01:11:59.619 --> 01:12:00.962
Then. who is?

869
01:12:01.116 --> 01:12:03.727
We're trying to protect
you people from them.

870
01:12:03.879 --> 01:12:06.492
The only thing we do kill.

871
01:12:08.372 --> 01:12:10.217
Vampires.

872
01:12:11.060 --> 01:12:11.867
Jake. you can't...

873
01:12:11.905 --> 01:12:14.324
Don't worry. we can't touch your
little precious Cullens.

874
01:12:14.401 --> 01:12:17.013
Unless they violate the Treaty.

875
01:12:17.281 --> 01:12:19.125
It's not what I'm saying.

876
01:12:19.585 --> 01:12:22.196
You can't kill vampires. though.

877
01:12:22.618 --> 01:12:25.038
They will kill you.
- Really?

878
01:12:25.113 --> 01:12:28.071
We took out that leech with
the dreads easy enough.

879
01:12:31.950 --> 01:12:32.756
Laurent?

880
01:12:32.909 --> 01:12:34.869
And his redhead girlfriend is next.

881
01:12:35.059 --> 01:12:37.900
Vic... Victoria is here?
- Was.

882
01:12:37.978 --> 01:12:40.205
We chased her all the way to the
Canadian border the other night.

883
01:12:40.244 --> 01:12:41.742
But she keeps coming back.

884
01:12:41.818 --> 01:12:45.081
We don't know what she's after.
- I do.

885
01:12:48.383 --> 01:12:49.844
Me.

886
01:12:57.906 --> 01:13:00.940
Don't worry.
we've got this place covered.

887
01:13:01.285 --> 01:13:03.359
She wont get near you or Charlie.

888
01:13:04.358 --> 01:13:05.894
But you gotta be careful.

889
01:13:06.046 --> 01:13:09.042
She's fast. you don't know.
how fast she is.

890
01:13:09.158 --> 01:13:12.459
You know. your lack of confidence
in us is a little insulting.

891
01:13:14.188 --> 01:13:16.338
Alright. I better go.

892
01:13:17.298 --> 01:13:20.831
And you gotta go.
- Yeah.

893
01:13:21.406 --> 01:13:23.556
I got a vampire to kill.

894
01:13:36.843 --> 01:13:39.838
<i>Alice. I'm alright.</i>

895
01:13:40.798 --> 01:13:42.602
<i>Until I'm alone.</i>

896
01:13:43.716 --> 01:13:46.135
<i>And lately.
that's all the time.</i>

897
01:13:46.366 --> 01:13:48.977
<i>Jacob's gone.
he's hunting for Victoria.</i>

898
01:13:49.130 --> 01:13:51.204
<i>And Charlie is hunting Jacob.</i>

899
01:13:51.511 --> 01:13:52.816
<i>And you're gone.</i>

900
01:13:53.892 --> 01:13:56.196
<i>And so is Edward.</i>

901
01:13:59.269 --> 01:14:01.416
<i>And I just have nothing now.</i>

902
01:14:04.720 --> 01:14:06.564
You got something. Harry?

903
01:14:07.792 --> 01:14:09.750
Nope. nothing.

904
01:14:16.700 --> 01:14:18.391
<i>But I realize where I have to go.</i>

905
01:14:18.544 --> 01:14:20.655
<i>What I have to do
to see him again.</i>

906
01:17:11.951 --> 01:17:13.641
<i>Don't do this.</i>

907
01:17:17.942 --> 01:17:20.168
You wanted me to be human.

908
01:17:22.434 --> 01:17:24.315
Watch me.

909
01:17:26.505 --> 01:17:29.614
<i>Please? For me?</i>

910
01:17:29.768 --> 01:17:31.995
You won't stay with me
any other way.

911
01:17:35.221 --> 01:17:37.294
<i>Bella. Please.</i>

912
01:19:01.540 --> 01:19:02.999
<i>Breathe!</i>

913
01:19:04.651 --> 01:19:06.110
<i>Breathe!</i>

914
01:19:07.147 --> 01:19:09.374
Come on. Bella.
Breathe.

915
01:19:15.632 --> 01:19:18.628
Bella?
Bella. can you hear me?

916
01:19:24.196 --> 01:19:25.655
Jake.

917
01:19:33.487 --> 01:19:36.367
What the hell were you thinking. huh?

918
01:19:36.790 --> 01:19:38.825
I just needed to see something.

919
01:19:39.555 --> 01:19:40.476
Take her home.

920
01:19:40.592 --> 01:19:42.818
I'm gonna go help over at Harry's place.

921
01:19:45.891 --> 01:19:47.733
What happened at Harry's?

922
01:19:48.080 --> 01:19:50.191
Harry Clearwater had a heart attack.

923
01:19:51.420 --> 01:19:53.840
Charlie and my Dad are at Harry's place
with his family.

924
01:19:53.917 --> 01:19:58.178
Is he okay?
- He's gone.

925
01:20:02.287 --> 01:20:05.166
Come on. I'll give you sØmething to dry
and drive you home.

926
01:20:16.340 --> 01:20:18.453
Hundred and eight degrees over here.

927
01:20:20.642 --> 01:20:21.832
God!

928
01:20:22.906 --> 01:20:24.787
My hands are freezing.

929
01:20:26.594 --> 01:20:28.820
It must be nice. never getting cold.

930
01:20:29.358 --> 01:20:33.120
Its a wolf thing.
- It's not.

931
01:20:33.851 --> 01:20:37.613
Its a Jacob thing.
Youre just warm.

932
01:20:39.956 --> 01:20:42.068
You're like. your own sun.

933
01:20:45.563 --> 01:20:49.708
This is better.
Now that you know about me.

934
01:20:52.282 --> 01:20:53.856
But...?

935
01:20:58.426 --> 01:21:00.767
You saw what happened to Emily.

936
01:21:04.031 --> 01:21:05.491
Sam got angry.

937
01:21:06.335 --> 01:21:08.601
...lost it for a split second...

938
01:21:09.599 --> 01:21:11.941
...Em was standing too close.

939
01:21:13.939 --> 01:21:16.281
He will never be able
to take that back.

940
01:21:19.044 --> 01:21:20.889
What if I get mad at you?

941
01:21:32.178 --> 01:21:34.558
Sometimes...

942
01:21:36.018 --> 01:21:38.244
I feel like. I'm gonna disappear.

943
01:21:44.656 --> 01:21:46.501
You need not hear it from me.

944
01:21:51.416 --> 01:21:54.987
But I always will.
You're not gonna loose yourself.

945
01:21:57.559 --> 01:21:59.671
I won't let that happen.

946
01:22:01.899 --> 01:22:03.088
How?

947
01:22:06.275 --> 01:22:08.695
I'll tell you all the time.

948
01:22:12.189 --> 01:22:14.032
How special you are.

949
01:22:32.578 --> 01:22:34.038
Thank you...

950
01:22:34.306 --> 01:22:35.766
...for everything.

951
01:22:41.602 --> 01:22:43.061
Wait!

952
01:22:45.251 --> 01:22:48.513
There's a vampire.
- How do you know?

953
01:22:49.129 --> 01:22:51.548
I can smell it.
I'm getting you out.

954
01:22:53.006 --> 01:22:54.697
That's Carlisle's car!

955
01:22:56.078 --> 01:22:57.268
Theyre here.

956
01:22:57.767 --> 01:22:59.995
Bella. it's a trick. Stop!

957
01:23:00.263 --> 01:23:01.723
You gotta come with me.

958
01:23:04.488 --> 01:23:06.062
They won't hurt me.

959
01:23:06.138 --> 01:23:09.249
If a Cullen is back here.
this is their territory.

960
01:23:09.941 --> 01:23:12.361
The treaty says we can only
defend our own lands.

961
01:23:12.398 --> 01:23:16.045
I can't protect you here.
- Okay. it's okay. You don't have to.

962
01:23:18.541 --> 01:23:21.806
Youre about to cross a line.
- Then don't draw one.

963
01:23:22.535 --> 01:23:24.110
Please.

964
01:23:39.852 --> 01:23:42.081
Alice!
- You're dead!

965
01:23:42.271 --> 01:23:43.961
Bella?
- What are you...?

966
01:23:44.461 --> 01:23:47.457
I'm sorry. I just...
I can't believe you're here.

967
01:23:47.647 --> 01:23:48.570
Is... Is...?

968
01:23:48.607 --> 01:23:51.334
Would you like to explain to me
how you're alive?

969
01:23:52.333 --> 01:23:55.212
What?
- I saw a vision of you.

970
01:23:55.366 --> 01:23:57.208
You jumped off a cliff.

971
01:23:57.362 --> 01:23:59.474
Why in the hell would you try
and kill yourself?

972
01:23:59.589 --> 01:24:02.853
I mean. what about Charlie? What about...?
- I didn't try to kill myself.

973
01:24:03.428 --> 01:24:04.889
I was cliff jumping.

974
01:24:05.042 --> 01:24:06.347
Recreationally!

975
01:24:06.655 --> 01:24:08.305
It was fun.

976
01:24:10.188 --> 01:24:14.450
I have never met anyone more prone
to life-threatening idiocy.

977
01:24:20.939 --> 01:24:24.049
Did you... did you tell him?
- No.

978
01:24:25.470 --> 01:24:28.580
He only calls once in a few months.

979
01:24:29.771 --> 01:24:31.998
He said he wants to be alone.

980
01:24:37.373 --> 01:24:41.406
Aw. what is that
God awful wet dog smell?

981
01:24:43.825 --> 01:24:45.667
That's probably me.

982
01:24:46.590 --> 01:24:49.315
Or... it's Jacob.

983
01:24:49.853 --> 01:24:51.543
Jacob who?

984
01:24:52.349 --> 01:24:54.960
Jacob's kind of a werewolf.

985
01:24:55.383 --> 01:24:59.376
Ugh! Bella! Werewolf's are not
good company to keep!

986
01:25:00.298 --> 01:25:02.140
Speak for yourself.

987
01:25:06.863 --> 01:25:08.975
I had to see if you were safe.

988
01:25:10.127 --> 01:25:12.547
I thought you couldn't protect me here.

989
01:25:13.123 --> 01:25:14.813
Guess. I don't care.

990
01:25:18.382 --> 01:25:20.495
Well. I'm not gonna hurt her.

991
01:25:22.184 --> 01:25:23.874
No. you're just a harmless Cullen.

992
01:25:23.989 --> 01:25:25.449
We're talking about
the other bloodsucker...

993
01:25:25.526 --> 01:25:27.445
...who tried to kill Bella
because of you.

994
01:25:27.523 --> 01:25:30.402
Victoria?
- Yeah. Victoria has been around.

995
01:25:30.633 --> 01:25:32.475
I didn't see her.

996
01:25:32.975 --> 01:25:35.548
I didn't see you getting pulled out
of the water either.

997
01:25:37.275 --> 01:25:40.155
I can't see past you
and your pack of mutts!

998
01:25:40.231 --> 01:25:42.958
Don't get me upset.
- Hey. stop!

999
01:25:43.034 --> 01:25:45.646
Things are gonna get very ugly!
- Stop! Stop! Stop!

1000
01:25:51.367 --> 01:25:53.978
I will give you a minute.

1001
01:26:00.929 --> 01:26:04.116
You're going anywhere.
you're gonna come back. right?

1002
01:26:04.192 --> 01:26:06.036
As soon as you put the dog out.

1003
01:26:14.944 --> 01:26:16.787
Is he...?

1004
01:26:20.013 --> 01:26:20.819
Are there others?

1005
01:26:20.973 --> 01:26:23.276
How many Cullens are here
and how long are they staying?

1006
01:26:23.853 --> 01:26:25.043
No.

1007
01:26:25.656 --> 01:26:27.500
It's just Alice.

1008
01:26:32.031 --> 01:26:34.258
And she can stay
as long as she like.

1009
01:26:36.946 --> 01:26:39.058
Are the rest coming back?

1010
01:26:45.278 --> 01:26:46.738
No.

1011
01:26:48.159 --> 01:26:49.848
Not that I know of.

1012
01:26:50.541 --> 01:26:52.229
Anything else?

1013
01:26:56.145 --> 01:26:57.721
That's it.

1014
01:26:59.639 --> 01:27:02.634
Well. if that's all. then you better go
run back to Sam.

1015
01:27:05.899 --> 01:27:07.742
I have done it again.

1016
01:27:08.894 --> 01:27:11.313
I keep breaking my promise.

1017
01:27:15.652 --> 01:27:18.263
We don't have to do this to each other.

1018
01:27:22.564 --> 01:27:24.407
Yes. we do.

1019
01:27:35.620 --> 01:27:37.309
Bella...

1020
01:27:40.841 --> 01:27:42.991
Stay with me forever.

1021
01:27:58.773 --> 01:28:00.463
Swan Residence.

1022
01:28:05.955 --> 01:28:07.797
He's not here right now.

1023
01:28:08.680 --> 01:28:10.639
He's arranging a funeral.

1024
01:28:25.615 --> 01:28:27.073
Who is that?

1025
01:28:27.726 --> 01:28:30.337
What?
- Always in the way.

1026
01:28:32.410 --> 01:28:35.138
Who was that?
- Bella. step back.

1027
01:28:35.291 --> 01:28:36.865
Jacob. who was that?
- Stop.

1028
01:28:37.209 --> 01:28:38.669
Bella. it's Edward.

1029
01:28:38.899 --> 01:28:40.091
He thinks you are dead.

1030
01:28:40.205 --> 01:28:42.701
Rosalie told him.
why I came here.

1031
01:28:44.430 --> 01:28:45.350
Why would you...?

1032
01:28:45.427 --> 01:28:47.078
Why didn't you let me speak to him?

1033
01:28:47.155 --> 01:28:48.999
He didn't ask for you.
- I don't care!

1034
01:28:49.114 --> 01:28:51.725
Bella. he's going to the Volturi.

1035
01:28:52.378 --> 01:28:54.221
He wants to die too.

1036
01:28:56.486 --> 01:28:59.021
He left you. Bella.
He didn't want you anymore. remember?

1037
01:28:59.098 --> 01:29:02.208
But I'm not gonna let him
kill himself out of guilt.

1038
01:29:03.130 --> 01:29:04.705
What about your Dad?

1039
01:29:05.510 --> 01:29:06.432
I'm eighteen.

1040
01:29:06.546 --> 01:29:08.659
I'm legally free to go.
And I left a note.

1041
01:29:10.541 --> 01:29:11.999
Please. Bella.

1042
01:29:13.419 --> 01:29:15.916
Just... stay here.

1043
01:29:17.144 --> 01:29:18.988
Not for Charlie.

1044
01:29:21.176 --> 01:29:23.020
For me...

1045
01:29:23.558 --> 01:29:25.401
I gotta go.

1046
01:29:30.738 --> 01:29:32.581
I'm begging you.

1047
01:29:35.000 --> 01:29:36.843
Please.

1048
01:29:38.149 --> 01:29:39.991
Bye. Jacob.

1049
01:29:47.825 --> 01:29:49.284
Okay.

1050
01:30:47.880 --> 01:30:49.992
So you made up your mind?

1051
01:30:50.300 --> 01:30:53.180
I'm afraid your particular gifts...

1052
01:30:53.909 --> 01:30:56.520
...are too valuable
to destroy.

1053
01:30:56.864 --> 01:31:00.130
But if you're unhappy
with your lot.

1054
01:31:00.706 --> 01:31:02.394
...join us.

1055
01:31:02.702 --> 01:31:06.582
We would be delighted
to utilize your skills.

1056
01:31:07.080 --> 01:31:09.690
Won't you consider
staying with us?

1057
01:31:11.380 --> 01:31:13.338
You know what will happen anyway.

1058
01:31:13.607 --> 01:31:16.218
Not without cause.

1059
01:31:19.522 --> 01:31:21.363
Such a waste.

1060
01:31:27.739 --> 01:31:29.427
I'm guessing you didn't rent this car?

1061
01:31:29.580 --> 01:31:31.693
I figured. you wouldn't be
opposed to grand theft auto.

1062
01:31:31.770 --> 01:31:33.230
Not today.

1063
01:31:36.032 --> 01:31:39.297
What? What are you seeing?
- They refused him.

1064
01:31:39.719 --> 01:31:42.138
So...?
- He's gonna make a scene.

1065
01:31:42.291 --> 01:31:45.172
Show himself to the humans.
- No! When?

1066
01:31:46.054 --> 01:31:48.781
He's gonna wait until noon.
when the sun's at it's highest.

1067
01:31:51.507 --> 01:31:54.501
Alice. you gotta hurry up.
- There's Volterra.

1068
01:32:18.385 --> 01:32:21.036
Why are they all in red?
- San Marcos Day festival.

1069
01:32:21.226 --> 01:32:23.954
They're commemorating the expulsion
of the vampires from the city.

1070
01:32:24.108 --> 01:32:25.297
It's the perfect setting.

1071
01:32:25.374 --> 01:32:27.794
The Volturi will never let him
get far enough to reveal himself.

1072
01:32:27.908 --> 01:32:32.055
We have 5 minutes.
- You know. Bella? Breathe.

1073
01:32:38.123 --> 01:32:38.660
Alice?!

1074
01:32:38.736 --> 01:32:40.849
Bella. you're the only one
he can't see coming.

1075
01:32:40.963 --> 01:32:42.038
If I go. he will read my thoughts...

1076
01:32:42.077 --> 01:32:43.921
...he'll think I'm lying
and rush into it.

1077
01:32:44.649 --> 01:32:46.493
Where do I go?
- He'll be under the clock tower.

1078
01:32:46.531 --> 01:32:47.722
Go!

1079
01:34:35.622 --> 01:34:37.196
No!

1080
01:34:38.693 --> 01:34:39.883
Heaven.

1081
01:34:40.077 --> 01:34:41.766
You have to move!

1082
01:34:42.380 --> 01:34:45.260
Open your eyes. look at me.
I'm alive.

1083
01:34:45.683 --> 01:34:47.526
You have to move!

1084
01:34:48.216 --> 01:34:49.676
Bella?

1085
01:34:56.588 --> 01:34:59.198
You're here.
- Yeah.

1086
01:35:01.272 --> 01:35:02.962
You're alive!

1087
01:35:05.881 --> 01:35:07.339
Yes.

1088
01:35:15.939 --> 01:35:18.282
I needed you to see me once.

1089
01:35:19.742 --> 01:35:23.312
You had to know that I was alive.
You didn't have to feel guilty or anything.

1090
01:35:26.692 --> 01:35:30.339
I can let you go now.

1091
01:35:33.718 --> 01:35:35.946
You never had to let it go.

1092
01:35:38.020 --> 01:35:41.130
I just couldn't live in a world
where you don't exist.

1093
01:35:42.819 --> 01:35:45.238
But you said...
- I lied.

1094
01:35:45.659 --> 01:35:48.925
I had to lie
and you believe me so easily.

1095
01:35:53.801 --> 01:35:57.564
Because it doesn't make sense
for you to love me.

1096
01:35:59.792 --> 01:36:03.594
I'm nothing... human.
Nothing.

1097
01:36:04.437 --> 01:36:08.585
Bella. you're everything to me.

1098
01:36:09.775 --> 01:36:11.619
Everything.

1099
01:36:36.078 --> 01:36:38.114
I won't be needing your services
after all. gentlemen.

1100
01:36:38.151 --> 01:36:39.995
Aro wants to speak with you again.

1101
01:36:40.224 --> 01:36:41.299
No rules were broken.

1102
01:36:41.416 --> 01:36:43.373
Nevertheless. we should take this
conversation...

1103
01:36:43.450 --> 01:36:45.370
...to a more appropriate venue.

1104
01:36:45.601 --> 01:36:47.175
Fine.

1105
01:36:47.981 --> 01:36:50.402
Bella. why don't you go enjoy
the rest of the festival?

1106
01:36:50.478 --> 01:36:53.587
The girl comes with us.
- No. You can go to hell.

1107
01:36:55.699 --> 01:36:58.695
Come on. guys.
It's a festival.

1108
01:36:58.772 --> 01:37:00.999
We wouldn't want to make a scene.

1109
01:37:01.460 --> 01:37:02.650
We wouldnt.

1110
01:37:03.187 --> 01:37:04.763
Enough!

1111
01:37:06.067 --> 01:37:07.257
Jane.

1112
01:37:07.718 --> 01:37:10.137
Aro send me to see
what's taking so long.

1113
01:37:18.507 --> 01:37:20.351
Just do as she says.

1114
01:37:32.370 --> 01:37:33.829
Go ahead.

1115
01:37:37.592 --> 01:37:39.051
Are you scared?

1116
01:37:40.165 --> 01:37:41.355
Are you?

1117
01:37:42.162 --> 01:37:43.353
No.

1118
01:38:14.224 --> 01:38:15.913
Good afternoon.

1119
01:38:20.176 --> 01:38:22.518
Is she human?
- Yes.

1120
01:38:25.322 --> 01:38:28.431
Does she know?
- Yes.

1121
01:38:28.816 --> 01:38:30.390
Then why would...

1122
01:38:32.079 --> 01:38:33.923
She wants to be...

1123
01:38:34.306 --> 01:38:37.187
And so she will be.
- Or dessert!

1124
01:38:45.403 --> 01:38:49.167
Sister. sent you out to get one
and you bring back two.

1125
01:38:49.627 --> 01:38:51.202
And a half.

1126
01:38:52.084 --> 01:38:53.353
Such a clever girl.

1127
01:38:53.505 --> 01:38:55.925
What a happy surprise!

1128
01:38:56.271 --> 01:38:59.382
Bella is alive after all.

1129
01:38:59.688 --> 01:39:02.951
Isn't that wonderful?

1130
01:39:03.337 --> 01:39:05.564
I love a happy ending.

1131
01:39:09.364 --> 01:39:11.476
They are so rare.

1132
01:39:15.125 --> 01:39:17.544
"La Tua Cantante. "
'Your Singer'

1133
01:39:17.696 --> 01:39:20.308
Your blood appeals to you
so much...

1134
01:39:21.153 --> 01:39:22.997
...it makes me thirsty.

1135
01:39:23.418 --> 01:39:26.030
How can you stand
to be so close to her?

1136
01:39:26.183 --> 01:39:29.178
It's not without difficulty.
- Yes. I can see that.

1137
01:39:32.404 --> 01:39:34.631
Aro can read every thought
I ever had.

1138
01:39:34.785 --> 01:39:36.244
With one touch.

1139
01:39:36.858 --> 01:39:38.701
And now you know everything.

1140
01:39:39.623 --> 01:39:41.081
So. get on with it.

1141
01:39:44.154 --> 01:39:48.032
You're quite soul reader yourself. Edward.

1142
01:39:48.838 --> 01:39:50.297
Though...

1143
01:39:50.720 --> 01:39:53.138
...you can't read Bella's thoughts.

1144
01:39:56.326 --> 01:39:58.168
Fascinating!

1145
01:40:01.164 --> 01:40:03.008
I would love to see if...

1146
01:40:03.736 --> 01:40:06.733
...you are an exception
to my gifts. as well.

1147
01:40:08.882 --> 01:40:10.725
Would you do me the honor?

1148
01:40:31.000 --> 01:40:32.575
Interesting.

1149
01:40:34.416 --> 01:40:36.260
I see nothing.

1150
01:40:44.938 --> 01:40:46.782
I wonder if...

1151
01:40:47.203 --> 01:40:50.582
Let's see if she is immune
to all our powers.

1152
01:40:51.390 --> 01:40:53.232
Shall we. Jane?

1153
01:40:54.846 --> 01:40:57.072
No!
- Pain.

1154
01:41:11.933 --> 01:41:13.391
Stop!

1155
01:41:13.968 --> 01:41:15.811
Stop. please!
Stop!

1156
01:41:16.349 --> 01:41:17.539
Stop!

1157
01:41:17.806 --> 01:41:19.651
Just stop hurting him. please!
Please!

1158
01:41:20.842 --> 01:41:22.299
Jane?

1159
01:41:24.221 --> 01:41:25.678
Master?

1160
01:41:29.403 --> 01:41:31.247
Go ahead. my dear.

1161
01:41:36.354 --> 01:41:38.198
This may hurt just a little.

1162
01:41:54.095 --> 01:41:55.938
Remarkable!

1163
01:41:57.512 --> 01:42:00.238
She confounds us all.

1164
01:42:00.621 --> 01:42:04.117
So. what we do with you now?

1165
01:42:04.270 --> 01:42:07.649
You already know
what you're going to do. Aro.

1166
01:42:08.186 --> 01:42:12.334
She knows too much.
she's a liability.

1167
01:42:16.173 --> 01:42:17.632
That's true.

1168
01:42:21.317 --> 01:42:23.007
Felix?

1169
01:43:26.212 --> 01:43:29.591
Please! No. no!
Please!

1170
01:43:32.049 --> 01:43:33.891
Kill me... kill me.

1171
01:43:34.198 --> 01:43:35.659
Not him.

1172
01:43:45.488 --> 01:43:48.560
How extraordinary.

1173
01:43:49.635 --> 01:43:52.246
You would give up your life...

1174
01:43:52.707 --> 01:43:54.549
...for someone like us.

1175
01:43:54.934 --> 01:43:56.547
A vampire.

1176
01:43:57.621 --> 01:44:00.002
A soulless monster.

1177
01:44:00.080 --> 01:44:01.922
Just get away from him!

1178
01:44:05.839 --> 01:44:08.298
You don't know a thing...

1179
01:44:09.371 --> 01:44:11.177
...about his soul.

1180
01:44:11.714 --> 01:44:18.587
Maybe it's one or the other.

1181
01:44:21.084 --> 01:44:23.272
This is a sadness.

1182
01:44:24.962 --> 01:44:29.032
If only it be your intention
to give her immortality.

1183
01:44:36.942 --> 01:44:38.402
Wait!

1184
01:44:39.706 --> 01:44:41.550
Bella will be one of us.

1185
01:44:43.316 --> 01:44:44.775
I've seen it.

1186
01:44:46.541 --> 01:44:48.385
I'll change her myself.

1187
01:45:20.793 --> 01:45:22.406
Mesmerizing!

1188
01:45:22.560 --> 01:45:24.787
To see. what you have seen.

1189
01:45:25.632 --> 01:45:27.858
Before it is happened.

1190
01:45:30.009 --> 01:45:31.544
Your gifts...

1191
01:45:31.890 --> 01:45:34.847
...will make for an intriguing...

1192
01:45:35.307 --> 01:45:37.150
...immortal.

1193
01:45:37.536 --> 01:45:40.453
Isabella.

1194
01:45:43.832 --> 01:45:45.368
Go now.

1195
01:45:45.829 --> 01:45:47.748
Make your preparations.

1196
01:45:48.364 --> 01:45:50.973
Let's be done with this.

1197
01:45:52.203 --> 01:45:54.891
Heidi will arrive. any moment.

1198
01:45:56.118 --> 01:45:57.963
Thank you...

1199
01:45:58.193 --> 01:46:00.957
...for the visit.
- We'll return the favØr.

1200
01:46:01.035 --> 01:46:02.186
I would advise...

1201
01:46:02.417 --> 01:46:06.181
...that you follow through on your promise soon.
We do not offer second chances.

1202
01:46:07.831 --> 01:46:09.021
Goodbye...

1203
01:46:09.214 --> 01:46:11.094
...my young friends.

1204
01:46:16.931 --> 01:46:18.468
<i>Nice fishing. Heidi.</i>

1205
01:46:18.775 --> 01:46:20.771
<i>Yes. they do look rather juicy.</i>

1206
01:46:20.925 --> 01:46:22.767
<i>Save some for me.</i>

1207
01:46:23.536 --> 01:46:26.839
<i>This way. please.
Stay together.</i>

1208
01:46:52.181 --> 01:46:53.640
You're here.

1209
01:46:55.636 --> 01:46:57.210
You can sleep.

1210
01:47:00.628 --> 01:47:03.047
I'll still be here
when you wake up.

1211
01:47:06.696 --> 01:47:10.459
Bella. the only reason
that I left...

1212
01:47:11.381 --> 01:47:13.991
...was because I thought
I was protecting you.

1213
01:47:15.912 --> 01:47:18.601
I needed you to have a chance...

1214
01:47:18.677 --> 01:47:22.171
...at a normal. happy life.

1215
01:47:25.434 --> 01:47:27.853
It was so easy for you to leave.

1216
01:47:30.080 --> 01:47:33.959
Leaving you was the hardest thing
I've done in a 100 years.

1217
01:47:40.256 --> 01:47:42.100
I swear...

1218
01:47:42.867 --> 01:47:46.246
I will never fail you again.

1219
01:47:47.629 --> 01:47:49.471
I'm so sorry.

1220
01:47:51.393 --> 01:47:53.235
Charlie's coming.
- Hey!

1221
01:47:56.268 --> 01:47:57.842
You okay?

1222
01:47:59.110 --> 01:48:00.569
Fine.

1223
01:48:03.143 --> 01:48:05.253
Dad. you don't have to worry.

1224
01:48:05.830 --> 01:48:07.711
Yeah. last time you said that
you took off.

1225
01:48:07.788 --> 01:48:09.899
I didn't see you for three days.

1226
01:48:11.552 --> 01:48:13.778
I'm really sorry. Dad.

1227
01:48:15.007 --> 01:48:19.154
Bella. do not ever do that
to me again.

1228
01:48:21.265 --> 01:48:22.725
Ever.

1229
01:48:24.990 --> 01:48:26.680
And you're grounded...

1230
01:48:26.949 --> 01:48:29.367
...for the rest of your life.

1231
01:48:30.020 --> 01:48:31.480
Okay.

1232
01:48:41.195 --> 01:48:43.805
I'm not technically breaking
any of his rules.

1233
01:48:46.571 --> 01:48:49.565
He did say. I couldn't take a step
inside through the door.

1234
01:48:50.179 --> 01:48:52.024
I came in through the window.

1235
01:48:56.016 --> 01:48:58.243
He's not going to forgive me easily.

1236
01:49:00.663 --> 01:49:02.122
I know.

1237
01:49:03.888 --> 01:49:05.425
Can you?

1238
01:49:08.803 --> 01:49:10.723
I hope you can because...

1239
01:49:11.030 --> 01:49:14.179
I honestly don't know
how to live without you.

1240
01:49:18.326 --> 01:49:19.786
Come here.

1241
01:49:36.527 --> 01:49:40.520
Once Alice changes me.

1242
01:49:42.326 --> 01:49:44.284
...you can't get rid of me.

1243
01:49:45.436 --> 01:49:47.585
She won't need to change you.

1244
01:49:48.430 --> 01:49:51.196
There are always ways to keep
the Volturi in the dark.

1245
01:49:53.421 --> 01:49:54.765
No.

1246
01:49:55.189 --> 01:49:56.416
No!

1247
01:50:02.062 --> 01:50:04.288
You all know what I want.

1248
01:50:06.170 --> 01:50:09.935
And I know.
how much I'm asking for.

1249
01:50:11.278 --> 01:50:12.737
The only thing I can think of...
for...

1250
01:50:12.776 --> 01:50:14.502
...it to be fair is to just vote.

1251
01:50:14.695 --> 01:50:17.806
You don't know what you just...
- Just... shut up!

1252
01:50:19.264 --> 01:50:20.571
Alice?

1253
01:50:20.878 --> 01:50:23.220
I already consider you my sister.

1254
01:50:27.097 --> 01:50:28.711
Yes!
- Thank you.

1255
01:50:28.788 --> 01:50:30.208
I vote. yes.

1256
01:50:31.398 --> 01:50:34.662
It would be nice to not wanna
kill you all the time.

1257
01:50:37.772 --> 01:50:39.347
I'm sorry.

1258
01:50:40.805 --> 01:50:44.185
I'm really sorry. both of you.
for the way I've acted.

1259
01:50:44.378 --> 01:50:45.567
And I'm really grateful...

1260
01:50:45.644 --> 01:50:48.255
...that you were brave enough
to go and save my brother.

1261
01:50:50.021 --> 01:50:53.402
But this isn't a life
I would have chosen for myself.

1262
01:50:55.666 --> 01:50:58.776
And I wish that there had been
someone to vote no for me.

1263
01:51:02.001 --> 01:51:03.845
So... no.

1264
01:51:04.728 --> 01:51:06.571
I vote hell yeah!

1265
01:51:08.415 --> 01:51:10.680
We can pick a fight with
these Volturi's some other way.

1266
01:51:10.756 --> 01:51:13.176
I already consider you.
a part of the family.

1267
01:51:14.250 --> 01:51:15.710
Yes!

1268
01:51:20.971 --> 01:51:22.930
Why are you doing this to me?

1269
01:51:24.811 --> 01:51:27.921
You know what this means.
- You've chosen not to live without her.

1270
01:51:28.035 --> 01:51:29.880
...which leaves me no choice.

1271
01:51:30.493 --> 01:51:32.338
I won't lose my son.

1272
01:51:38.327 --> 01:51:40.670
<i>I'll wait until after graduation...</i>

1273
01:51:40.747 --> 01:51:42.973
<i>...to make it easier on Charlie.</i>

1274
01:51:47.043 --> 01:51:49.616
I want you to be the one
to do it.

1275
01:51:56.451 --> 01:51:58.293
He wants to talk to me.

1276
01:52:01.251 --> 01:52:02.710
See. you're still alive for now.

1277
01:52:02.903 --> 01:52:05.013
He thinks. it's me keeping you away.

1278
01:52:05.360 --> 01:52:07.472
You stay the hell out of my head.

1279
01:52:08.892 --> 01:52:10.083
Jacob...

1280
01:52:10.926 --> 01:52:12.886
...I know you have
something to say to me.

1281
01:52:14.537 --> 01:52:17.147
But I wanna say something to you first.
If that's alright?

1282
01:52:19.260 --> 01:52:20.720
Thank you.

1283
01:52:23.637 --> 01:52:26.055
Thank you for keeping
Bella alive when...

1284
01:52:26.286 --> 01:52:27.169
...I didnt.

1285
01:52:27.400 --> 01:52:30.012
No. you didn't.

1286
01:52:31.240 --> 01:52:33.659
And it wasn't for your benefit.
trust me.

1287
01:52:33.850 --> 01:52:35.541
I'm still grateful.

1288
01:52:36.347 --> 01:52:37.268
But I'm here now.

1289
01:52:37.423 --> 01:52:40.033
And I'm not gonna leave her side
till she orders me away.

1290
01:52:40.188 --> 01:52:41.646
We'll see.

1291
01:52:44.219 --> 01:52:46.944
Hey. my turn to talk.

1292
01:52:50.708 --> 01:52:53.319
I'm here to remind you about
a key point in the Treaty.

1293
01:52:54.241 --> 01:52:55.816
I haven't forgotten.

1294
01:52:56.199 --> 01:52:57.389
What key point?

1295
01:52:57.696 --> 01:53:02.612
If any of them bites a human.
the truce is over.

1296
01:53:03.725 --> 01:53:05.568
But if I choose it.
it has nothing to do with you.

1297
01:53:05.645 --> 01:53:08.256
No... No. I won't let you.

1298
01:53:09.023 --> 01:53:11.251
You're not gonna be
one of them. Bella.

1299
01:53:11.405 --> 01:53:13.248
It's not up to you.

1300
01:53:13.939 --> 01:53:15.399
You know what we'll do to you.

1301
01:53:15.475 --> 01:53:17.818
I won't have choice.
- Bella. please come.

1302
01:53:17.894 --> 01:53:19.353
Wait.

1303
01:53:21.080 --> 01:53:23.039
Is he gonna hurt me?
Read his mind.

1304
01:53:30.643 --> 01:53:32.369
Jake...

1305
01:53:38.283 --> 01:53:40.205
I love you.

1306
01:53:44.235 --> 01:53:46.193
So. please...

1307
01:53:50.186 --> 01:53:52.145
DØn't make me choose.

1308
01:53:57.597 --> 01:53:59.442
Because it'll be him.

1309
01:54:02.667 --> 01:54:04.780
It's always been him.

1310
01:54:11.729 --> 01:54:13.571
Bella...

1311
01:54:20.445 --> 01:54:23.171
Goodbye. Jacob.
- No. you don't speak for her!

1312
01:54:28.009 --> 01:54:29.470
Bella. get out of here.

1313
01:54:31.656 --> 01:54:32.848
Stop!

1314
01:54:34.806 --> 01:54:36.149
Stop!

1315
01:54:36.420 --> 01:54:39.030
You can't hurt each other
without hurting me.

1316
01:54:57.693 --> 01:54:59.151
Jake?

1317
01:55:13.051 --> 01:55:14.624
He's right.

1318
01:55:15.394 --> 01:55:17.275
You shouldn't become one of us.

1319
01:55:22.344 --> 01:55:24.186
I can't do this alone.

1320
01:55:27.106 --> 01:55:28.947
Then please just wait.

1321
01:55:35.630 --> 01:55:38.893
Just give me... five years.

1322
01:55:43.502 --> 01:55:45.343
It's too long.

1323
01:55:49.529 --> 01:55:51.373
Then. three?

1324
01:55:55.328 --> 01:55:57.171
You're so stubborn.

1325
01:55:58.862 --> 01:56:00.703
What are you waiting for?

1326
01:56:09.266 --> 01:56:13.029
I have one condition...

1327
01:56:14.489 --> 01:56:17.099
...if you want me
to do it myself.

1328
01:56:20.709 --> 01:56:22.552
What's the condition?

1329
01:56:23.051 --> 01:56:24.895
And then. forever.

1330
01:56:26.699 --> 01:56:28.542
That's what I'm asking.

1331
01:56:39.102 --> 01:56:41.521
Marry me. Bella.
